con1-text_emo1: I bought a subscription to Showtime for 1 year because there is a show that I wanted to watch on it. I figured the $99 dollar price for one year was not too terrible. I am joyful that I get to watch that show because I thoroughly enjoy it. I am also joyful to notice that there are a few horror films that I have been wanting to see, which were not on any other streaming services that I have. However, I am certainly disappointed with the functioning of the app. It is unorganized, glitchy, only has a few select options (one profile for example), and does not have a very large library. Further, I am disappointed that they have a HUB right on the main screen for after-hours content (such as porn), without having any parental control features or multiple profile options so I can safeguard my child from seeing this content.

However, being "Showtime" and costing $99 for the year, I did not get what I wanted because I had higher expectations for the functionality and content of the service.
con1-text_pleasant: Neutral because I do not exactly consider relaxing and killing downtime by streaming content as being "pleasant." However, it is not exactly "unpleasant" either.

con1-text_emo1: The dicision to purchase the vaccum was a difficult one because it was so expensive. We did our research and were confident that Dyson was a good brand and would stand behind their product. We ended up putting the purchase on a credit card, which did cause a little bit of regret. However, when we used the vacuum for the first time, we were amazed at how easy it was to use and how well it worked. We are not as young as we used to be, and even vacuuming can sometimes be difficult. We were very thankful that we had the opportunity to purchase the Dyson, even though we had to put it on a charge card. We have used similar vaccums in the past, but none of them compared to the Dyson's performance and ease of use. I don't remember if the previous page listed grateful or thankful. To me these mean the same thing, and we were very thankful that we had the ability to purchase a quality product that will make our lives a little easier.
con1-text_emo2: I must have combined the answers on the previous page, but I will restate it here. As I'm getting older, it's become more difficult for me to carry, push, and pull a heavy vacuum cleaner around the house. This Dyson model is powerful and lighweight. Because of this, it makes vacuuming the house much, much easier, perhaps even a little bit fun! It was much more expensive than I ever would have considered paying in the past. In fact, we couldn't afford the purchase price all at once, so we ended up purchasing it with a charge card. We were very thankful that we had the opportunity to do so, because we were extremely pleased with the Dyson.
con1-text_importance: Yes, because it is a quality product that makes cleaning much, much easier. No other vacuum cleaner has performed as well as this one has.
con1-text_goalsCon: Yes, because we wanted a vacuum cleaner that was easier to use than our old, heavy vacuum. This Dyson is small and lightweight, but still has a cleaning power that is better than any other vacuum we have used previously.
con1-text_pleasant: Yes, because in addition to being easy to use and effective, it is innovative and kind of fun to use. The Dyson has a digital readout that shows you how many dust particles you have clean, including their sizes. For bare floors, there is even a little laser light that highlights the dust on the floor ahead of the cleaner tool. The Dyson is a great vacuum without these things, but the unique innovations on this model make cleaning a little bit fun.
con1-text_expect: Unexpected because it exceeded our expectations. Usually unexpected performance of a product is a bad thing, but it was definitely good in this case. From our research, we had expected it to be easier to use and effective, but we were blown away by how well it actually performed and how enjoyable it is to use.
con1-other_Text_emo: Guilt, because of the cost and having to use a charge card.

con2-text_pleasant: No, because I lost money and confidence in the mechanic's ability to do the job properly. I was also still not able to use my car.
con2-text_expect: Unexpected because my car was not fixed properly as promised, and I lost money.

con1-text_emo1:
An amazing vacation I had on this tropical island. Life was getting way too crazy with work and all the stress, so when I got the chance to escape to paradise, I couldn't believe my luck. Man, I was overflowing with gratitude!

I planned every single detail, searching online for the perfect spot, the coolest hotel, and the most epic activities. Just thinking about those palm-fringed beaches, the crystal-clear water, and the gentle ocean breeze had me feeling all warm and fuzzy inside. And when the day finally came, stepping onto that airplane, I was like, "Thank you, universe!" I was so grateful for this opportunity to disconnect from the real world and just soak up all the beauty and peace around me. It was pure magic!
con1-text_emo2:
Firstly, being able to take a break from the hectic routine of work and daily life allowed me to unwind and recharge both physically and mentally. It was a chance to escape the never-ending to-do lists, deadlines, and obligations, and simply focus on my own well-being.

Moreover, the surroundings and experiences on the vacation filled me with awe and appreciation. The tropical island's natural beauty, with its stunning beaches, clear blue waters, and lush greenery, was a sight to behold. Each day brought new adventures and opportunities to explore the wonders of nature, whether it was snorkeling among vibrant coral reefs or hiking through breathtaking rainforests.
con1-text_importance:
The vacation was important to me because it offered a much-needed break from my regular routine and allowed me to relax and recharge. It provided an opportunity to escape the stresses of work and daily life, giving me a chance to rejuvenate both physically and mentally. The change of scenery and the chance to explore a new destination added an element of excitement and adventure, making the vacation a valuable and cherished experience.

However, it is also important to note that the vacation might not be crucial in every aspect of my life. While it provided temporary respite and enjoyment, its long-term impact on my overall well-being might be limited. The vacation was just a temporary escape and did not address deeper issues or challenges that I might be facing. In that sense, the vacation's importance is neutral because it served as a valuable break, but its significance might be limited to the specific time period in which it occurred.
con1-text_goalsCon:
Yes, because the vacation was consistent with what I wanted.

The vacation aligned with my desires and expectations, making it a fulfilling experience. I had researched and planned the trip meticulously, ensuring that the destination, accommodations, and activities matched my preferences. The tropical island setting, with its beautiful beaches and serene atmosphere, was exactly what I had envisioned for a relaxing getaway.

Additionally, the activities and experiences available on the vacation were in line with my interests and desires. Whether it was snorkeling, hiking, or simply lounging by the beach, the vacation provided ample opportunities to engage in activities that I found enjoyable and fulfilling. The choices I made in planning the vacation resulted in an experience that was consistent with what I wanted, allowing me to fully immerse myself in the activities and surroundings that brought me joy and satisfaction.
con1-text_pleasant:
Yes, it was a very pleasant experience during the vacation. The tropical island setting with its stunning beaches and crystal-clear waters created a calming and beautiful atmosphere. I enjoyed engaging in various water sports, trying local cuisine, and just relaxing under the sun. All these activities were very fulfilling and brought a sense of happiness and contentment.

Spending quality time with loved ones also added to the pleasantness of the experience. We shared laughter, created memories, and had meaningful conversations. I also enjoyed some moments of solitude and personal reflection. These experiences deepened my sense of gratitude and made the vacation even more special. Overall, the vacation was a delightful and memorable experience that allowed me to escape from the stresses of daily life and indulge in moments of joy and relaxation.
con1-text_expect:
Well, not everything turned out to be exactly as I had expected. There were both expected and unexpected aspects of the experience.

Some things were expected because I had done thorough research and planning beforehand. The tropical island setting, the beautiful beaches, and the availability of water sports were all in line with my expectations. I anticipated moments of relaxation and enjoyment, and those expectations were met.

However, there were also unexpected elements that added a touch of surprise and excitement to the vacation. For instance, I didn't expect to stumble upon a hidden beach that wasn't mentioned in the guidebooks. It turned out to be a secluded paradise that felt like a personal discovery. Additionally, the locals' warm hospitality and friendliness exceeded my expectations, making the interactions more memorable and enjoyable. While some aspects aligned with my expectations, the unexpected surprises added a delightful twist to the vacation, making it even more memorable and fulfilling.
con2-text_emo1:
I remember feeling deeply disappointed during an expensive spa day that I had been eagerly anticipating. The spa's lackluster ambiance, outdated facilities, and crowded relaxation areas failed to create the serene atmosphere I had hoped for. Even worse, the treatments fell short of my expectations. The massage felt rushed and lacked the rejuvenating touch I had envisioned, while the facial left my skin feeling irritated instead of radiant. The stark contrast between my high expectations and the underwhelming reality left me feeling let down and regretful about the significant expense I had incurred.

The disappointment stemmed from the mismatch between the spa's reputation and the actual experience. The lack of attention to detail, subpar services, and unfulfilled promises left me feeling dissatisfied and questioning the value of the expensive spa day. It served as a reminder that price doesn't always guarantee quality, and it was a lesson learned about managing expectations when indulging in such luxurious experiences.
con2-text_emo2:
I felt disappointment during the spa day for several reasons. Firstly, the spa's ambiance and facilities were not up to par with the expectations set by its reputation and price point. The lackluster atmosphere, outdated decor, and overcrowded relaxation areas diminished the sense of tranquility and relaxation that I had hoped to experience. It was disheartening to realize that the luxurious environment I had anticipated was not reflected in the reality of the spa.

Secondly, the treatments themselves failed to meet my expectations. The massage felt hurried and lacked the attention and skill I had expected from a high-end spa. Instead of feeling rejuvenated, I was left feeling unsatisfied and disappointed. Similarly, the facial treatment, which I had hoped would leave my skin glowing, ended up causing irritation and falling short of the promised results. These subpar services further added to my disappointment and left me questioning the value of the expensive spa day.

The disappointment stemmed from the disparity between the expectations I had formed based on the spa's reputation and price, and the actual experience I encountered. The underwhelming ambiance, facilities, and treatments all contributed to my sense of disappointment and regret.
con2-text_importance:
Neutral because the spa day was important to me to some extent, but the experience fell short of my expectations.

The spa day held significance because I had been longing for a moment of relaxation and self-care. It was meant to be a treat, a chance to escape the stresses of daily life and indulge in pampering treatments. I was looking forward to rejuvenating my mind and body, expecting the spa to provide a much-needed break from the hustle and bustle. However, the disappointment I encountered during the actual experience made it less important in hindsight. The underwhelming ambiance, facilities, and treatments diminished the value and impact of the spa day. While it still offered a temporary escape, the unmet expectations and the hefty price tag made me question its overall importance in the long run.

Ultimately, the spa day held some level of importance as it represented a desire for self-care and relaxation. However, the letdown of the experience lessened its significance and made me reflect on the value of such indulgences. It served as a reminder that expectations should be managed, and that a high price doesn't always guarantee a satisfactory outcome.
con2-text_goalsCon:
No because the spa day was not consistent with what I wanted.

I had anticipated a luxurious and rejuvenating experience, but the reality of the spa day fell short of my expectations. The lackluster ambiance, outdated facilities, and overcrowded relaxation areas were not in line with what I had envisioned for a high-end spa. Additionally, the treatments themselves did not meet my expectations. The rushed massage and the facial that left my skin irritated were far from the relaxing and revitalizing experience I had hoped for. Overall, the spa day did not align with what I wanted in terms of a luxurious, indulgent, and rejuvenating escape.

The disappointment I felt stemmed from the mismatch between my desires and the actual experience. The inconsistency between my expectations and the reality of the spa day led to a sense of letdown and dissatisfaction. Instead of receiving the pampering and relaxation I had hoped for, the experience left me questioning the value and quality of the spa day.
con2-text_pleasant:
No,  the spa day was not a pleasant experience.

The lackluster ambiance, outdated facilities, and crowded relaxation areas detracted from the overall enjoyment of the experience. The underwhelming atmosphere and overcrowding created a sense of discomfort and hindered the relaxation I had sought. Moreover, the treatments themselves were disappointing, with a rushed massage and a facial that caused skin irritation. These factors contributed to a feeling of dissatisfaction and made the spa day far from pleasant.

Overall, the spa day failed to provide the expected level of enjoyment and relaxation. The subpar ambiance, facilities, and treatments all contributed to a negative experience. Instead of being a source of pleasure and rejuvenation, the spa day turned out to be a disappointment and left me feeling dissatisfied.
con2-text_expect:
No, not everything turned out to be what I had expected during the spa day.

I had expected a luxurious and rejuvenating experience, but several aspects fell short of my expectations. The ambiance, for example, was expected to be serene and inviting, but it turned out to be lackluster and outdated. The facilities, such as the jacuzzi and steam room, were also expected to be in good working condition, but I was disappointed to find out that the steam room was out of order. These unexpected discrepancies between my expectations and the actual state of the spa were disappointing and diminished the overall experience.

The quality of the treatments was also not as expected. I had anticipated skilled and attentive therapists providing relaxing massages and facials, but the experience felt rushed and lacked the desired level of expertise. This unexpected lack of quality in the treatments further added to my disappointment. Overall, the spa day did not fully align with my expectations, as certain aspects, both in terms of ambiance and treatment quality, turned out to be different than what I had anticipated.

con1-product: I bought an expensive ticket to see Taylor Swift in her EROS tour concert in Philadelphia
con1-text_emo1: As I entered the concert, I instantly felt a rush of tremendous joy, just to be in this huge stadium, filled with thousands of other jubilant people.  After Covid, this seemed to be a tremendous relief, especially since I could actually see the happiness reflected in all the faces.  Previously, I remembered seeing so much pain, fear and uncertainty in hospitals where people were dying from Covid.  So now, this felt right and good.  However, I have to admit I then experienced a rush of another not so positive emotion...guilt.  I realized the money I spent on my ticket could have helped many people.  It could have paid one month's rent, or went to pay a medical bill, or buy medicine , or buy food.  Fortunately, this guilt didn't last too long.  The sounds of the joy around me drowned out my guilt, and I experienced the fun I knew was mine.  I worked hard for the money I spent on my ticket, so I deserved to spend it however I wanted. I had the best time!
con1-text_emo2: I felt the guilt as a result of empathy that I feel for those who do not have the resources that I have.  However, I realized that I worked very hard and long to get what I have, so the guilt quickly subsided.
con1-text_importance: Yes because my granddaughter was given enough money to buy one ticket, but her mom wouldn't let her go alone.  So, I was able to buy my ticket and go with her.  The joy my granddaughter felt was priceless!  The guilt came as I did think I could have taught my granddaughter to give away her money to a better cause, but I didn't.  In the end, I was glad we went to see Swift!
con1-text_goalsCon: Yes because Swift's concert was probably the very best concert my granddaughter will ever remember. Sometimes, you have to go with the memories you can create.  I know she was over the moon with this experience, and I am thrilled that I was part of it!
con1-text_pleasant: This concert tour broke a lot of records.  Swift sang about 44 songs, and wore about 30 different outfits.  To  share the joy this brought to so many and be apart of it, was definitely worth it!
con1-text_expect: Expected because all the reviews were amazing!  Taylor definitely gave her all.  She loves her fans and puts on the best concert. She is young, energetic and she is worth the money!  This was the best show.

con1-text_emo1: Very specifically, it was when I launched the game Baldur's Gate 3 for my new gaming PC. I had tried to play the game on my old PC, which was almost 9 years old, and the game stuttered and crashed. My new PC played it effortlessly on "Ultra" graphical settings at a perfect 60 frames per second. It was a small moment, but in it I felt so grateful and relieved that I had made a purchase that served the function I needed it to so precisely. I also felt overwhelmingly grateful that I have reached a point in my life where I can afford the things that I want and that my life is in a place where I can drop what used to be an absurd amount of money on a gaming PC just for the pure entertainment and joy of it. I am a very lucky man.
con1-text_emo2: Using the gaming PC to play a demanding game on it's highest settings struck me with that feeling of overwhelming gratitude because it was a culmination of years of hard work and discipline paying off. It was a powerful reminder that my wife and family are successful and happy and I am achieving a kind of childhood dream and self actualization that I really strove for.
con1-text_importance: Yes because the PC serves not only as a gaming device for me, but also where I work and where the family enjoys nightly entertainment. We have our PC hooked up to our TV in the living room, so it serves as a central hub for work and leisure time. It goes beyond mere importance to being a central part of our life and success.
con1-text_goalsCon: Yes because not only is it a powerful gaming PC that plays the games I want it too, it also has the power inside to serve as a perfect tool for my work. I also made sure that, assuming things continue to work well and I maintain it, it should be relatively futureproof for the near future. I waited 9 years to upgrade my last PC, ideally I won't have to upgrade this one for a similar amount of time. It has been EXACTLY want I wanted it to be.
con1-text_pleasant: Yes because so far no matter what I've attempted to play or watch using this PC it has handled it easily. My wife and I are lifelong gamers, so to be able to play the latest and greatest effortlessly on this PC has been a dream come true, but it also easily plays 4k HDR 60fps movies, making my home theatre borderline unparalleled in terms of fidelity. Every time I use it (and I'm using it right now) I am pleased and grateful.
con1-text_expect: Unexpected because while I knew it would be powerful and fun, I did not expect it to be just as powerful as it is. With PC gaming there is a lot of tinkering you have to do to get things just right typically, but with this PC I can just set everything to max settings and it hums along perfectly. It's the first time in my life of being a tech junkie and gamer that I've have a machine that handled the stresses I've put it through with flying colors, that alone was unexpected.
con2-text_emo1: The installation of the floor went on for way longer than was expected, and the crew that was hired to do the work did a terrible job. It work was so bad, in fact, that they had to come redo a large section of it because it was installed incorrectly. During the redo, they stained a huge portion of the brand new floor.
con2-text_emo2: It became very clear to me that over the course of the installation, the crew that we hired were goofy failures who had no interest in doing a good job. They had swindled us and were charging us an exorbitant fee for subpar work. I grew angrier and angrier throughout the process until eventually we decided to just deal with the shoddy work lest we had a couple of moron in our house making things loud and dirty any longer.
con2-text_importance: Yes, because our old wood floor had started to break apart and drift and was not only looking ugly and bringing down the value of our home, but had also become dangerous by potentially causing slips or falls. A new floor was going to fix all those things.
con2-text_goalsCon: No because we wanted it done correctly, on time and on budget. It ended up being weeks longer than quoted and because we needed to take time off work to be home with the crew, it ended up costing us more money than we ever intended. Not only that, but the work itself was shoddy and there are stains left by the terrible work to this day.
con2-text_pleasant: No because the work they did needed to be done again, and even after the rework it is still messed up. Every day when I see the gunk and grime they left stuck and stained to what was supposed to be my brand new floor, I get angry again. It is a constant underfoot reminder of how I got swindled.
con2-text_expect: Unexpected because I had wanted a nice, pristine new wood floor to increase the attractiveness of my house and our overall happiness and safety. What I got was a decent looking floor that needs more work, and a massive headache from dealing with con men idiots.

con1-product: a gentleman came out and cleaned off my roof (moss, mold)
con1-text_emo1: We have a lot of roof cleaners in our area for the spring and summer, and one must watch out for who they hire.  I liked this guy's ad, and because he didn't use an entire page of the local paper, I decided to go with him.  I have a problem with businesses that buy one page out of the newspaper for their ads.  It just seems wrong to me.  Anyway, he came over and did not use a hose or any other type of cleaning device that I could see.  He was up on my roof or about 20 minutes and then knocked on my door and said he was done.  I asked him about it, and he said he uses some kind of other method to clean off roofs.  Since I wasn't able to see the roof, I just hoped he actually did something up there.  Next time I will hire the guy who has been advertising for years, and I know he uses a good washing hose to clear off moss and debris.
con1-text_emo2: Because it is a roof, I had no way to check out whether he did what he said he would.  The last guy who did my roof was up there for a couple of hours, and there was a lot of moss and debris on the ground.  That was 5 years ago.
con1-text_importance: Yea, it was extremely important.  I live in a very damp, snowy and cold climate.  The moss will completely eat your shingles if not kept clean.
con1-text_goalsCon: I am not sure.  I was quite shocked he didn't wash off the roof.
con1-text_pleasant: You can't say a clean roof is pleasant or unpleasant.  It is something that has to get done.
con1-text_expect: I expected a lot more than what he did.  I guess it was my fault for not being more assertive.  I have a problem with that.  Especially strangers who are at my house.

con2-text_emo2: I was excited about having the device, and was looking forward to getting it done and syncing it with my phone.
con2-text_importance: Yes because I don't feel that safe anymore in my neighborhood like I used to.
con2-text_goalsCon: Yes it was exactly what I wanted.  I feel safer now.  It was expensive for me because the device and chime for it were about $130, plus $75 for the tech. I also have a monthly payment for the device. But it was worth every penny.
con2-text_pleasant: Yes, it has been a lot of fun!  I am enjoying the alerts, and I know when someone is at the door.
con2-text_expect: Yes, everything has been what I expected.  There was one small glitch with the ring chime, and I called customer service, and they helped me out.

So I expected the food to taste much better. And they claim to offer an Italian experience, where you are treated like family, so I expected my experience to be as close to Italian as I though Italian should be. With such high expectations, if they had done even one thing wrong, it would have ruined the experience. But they did everything right and the food was delicious, so it made me very happy.
con1-text_importance: The food was important to me. I have an autoimmune disease which is very much affected by the food I eat. Eating as close to natural is important and is what I strive for. So when I find a restaurant that claims to use fresh ingredients, I put it on my list to try. We, as a family, eat out at least once or twice a week, so the restaurant choice is important to me. This particular restaurant claims to use fresh ingredients and cooks from scratch.
con1-text_goalsCon: Yes, because the restaurant uses fresh ingredients and cooks from scratch. This is exactly what I look for in a restaurant.
con1-text_pleasant: Yes, because the atmosphere and waitstaff at the restaurant met my expectations. And the food was delicious. So it all was a happy experience.
con1-text_expect: Expected because I expected them to have an Italian atmosphere and delicious food, and they met those expectations.

con1-text_emo1: the joy comes from the making of nifty things for the various games that i play, it multiplies the enjoyment i have for the hobbies i already have and i get to be excited about one of the coolest pieces of Tech ive ever owned. the regret comes in when i think about how much i spent, if i should have done something better, pay bills, save, etc. eventually i will make so many things thaat the device will "pay for itself" but i think ill always think about the initial cost

con1-text_emo1: I worked very hard to be able to afford the item and felt very proud of reaching my goal. It took years of sacrifice and determination to finally be able to enjoy the fruits of my labor. For example there were many times my friends wanted to go out and I would either be working extra hours or just stay home to save money. Took a lot of discipline to keep saying no to other temptations like cell phones, gaming systems, boats, etc... That said, I felt a little guilty knowing I just basically blew enough money for someone to buy a house in some states. I'm not blind to all the struggling families that have to choose between eating and putting gas in their car.
con1-text_emo2: It took so long to finally reach my goal. There were many nights I would come home exhausted and didn't want to do anything but go to bed. My physical health even suffered a bit from not getting enough sleep. I was just so proud of myself for seeing it through. The biggest thing was the morale boost of knowing I did it all by myself. On the other hand I see homeless people every day begging for anything they can get. And if they don't earn any money they go up and down the block digging in trash bins. It's a very sad reality. This makes me feel a bit guilty for spending so much money or something that serves no purpose other than self gratification.
con1-text_importance: In a way it was important but only as a status symbol. There's also a bit of nostalgia because I grew up loving them. I actually still own a few that are there simply for sentimental reasons. I also see it as a way to relax and unwind after working hard. I also enjoy the social element of bonding with old friends and making new ones. Suppose I could also make an argument it could be used for work but only slightly. On the flip side of things it's basically just a toy for adults. It doesn't really serve as a necessity. I don't need it to survive and it's virtually guaranteed to decrease in value is what it all boils down too.
con1-text_goalsCon: It's definitely what I wanted and expected it to be. When I use it I have a blast. It gets lots of attention wherever it goes and I have to admit there's a sense of pride showing it off.
con1-text_pleasant: Absolutely a pleasant experience. I get a huge rush every time I use it. The best part is the rush doesn't get old. I can always find a new experience that creates the same sense of pleasure. I suppose the biggest negative is it can be a little difficult to store and transport because of it's size so the total owner experience hasn't been enjoyable.
con1-text_expect: Yes. I actually got to test it out before owning it so I knew before I bought it but it's actually been better than expected because it's done all I need it to do and I haven't reached it's full capabilities.
con2-text_emo1: I paid a lot of money for a product that was all hype.
con2-text_emo2: I realized after I bought it that it wasn't worth what I paid for.
con2-text_importance: At first it was but only as a status symbol. I would later regret this.
con2-text_goalsCon: Kind of. It looked great just sitting there but it's performance was completely different
con2-text_pleasant: In a way it was pleasant as it got a lot of looks and compliments but fell way short when being able to deliver the promised performance.
con2-text_expect: No. I expected all the compliments(which it got), but didn't expect it to fall short on it's performance claims. When you advertise certain capabilities and charge $100k for the item then it doesn't even come close to delivering on promises it can be quite shocking.

con1-text_emo1:
It was something new to me - I of course have had keyboards, but this one was different: I bought it in parts and made it myself. The keys - the actual inside keys, not the caps that have the icons on them - had to be set in place and were a specific type that was best for me. The board I bought - so the actual main PCB - could be programmable, so I used that, the keys, and the frame to make a board that was just for me. I only have one hand, so having a keyboard tailored to my one-handedness, and was setup for a right hand only, was amazing. 

It made me so happy because it solved issues I have heard forever. I made do with a regular keyboard, sure, but there was a lot of concessions, not to mention all the movement with one hand was hard on my wrist. It turned it into an entirely different game, really, and while it was frustrating for a bit - as the key layout was totally different (it is right-handed dvorak), and the keycaps were blank - that was overturned by the sheer joy of having a keyboard set just for my situation.
con1-text_emo2: I suppose I already said this, but it is because it helped with problems I had been dealing with for over nine years. I made do with a regular keyboard, but it was not good on my wrist, and my efficiency was lower. This, however, fixed all of that, so it was kind of like being able to write on paper after only writing on cardboard for years.
con1-text_importance: Yes because, as noted, with only one hand, I had to go over the entire QWERTY keyboard with a right hand, when it was made for two hands. This keyboard was built for me, someone with only one hand, and in my case, the right hand. It helped bring me up to speed with those who are not disabled, and frankly, it has made me better than the average two hand keyboard users.
con1-text_goalsCon: Yes because it was built to be exactly what I wanted. I built it with all the parts and used a frame from I liked design wise. The PCB is the main product, and it worked as well as I was hoping. It has good firmware and software and I have not run in to any issues. I was able to tailor it to be EXACTLY what I wanted in a keyboard.
con1-text_pleasant: Yes because, again, it fixed issues I have dealt with for over nine years. It was made to be exactly what I needed, and I felt like I could finally type as well as I should have been. Of course, as I have mentioned, it took some getting used to, as the change was huge, but overall it was pleasant after I got past the initial hurdle of getting used to it.
con1-text_expect: Expected because I gathered the parts of the product and built it. I have said it a few times now, but again, the nature of the product is one that is very malleable - you can do whatever you want it. You can program it, you can swap keys, use different oil... I had expected it would be fine because of this, and it was. This product might be a bit different than some others, so my answers are repeating, but really, it is just a very customizable product, so the odds of it not being what you expected is low: I expected to be able to do what I want, and that turned out to be the case.
con2-text_emo1: It was... not easy to work with. I am an aviculturist, and one of my birds was very, very mean. He would chase the others around, pin them, and tear off their feathers. He never drew blood, but still - he had to go. I bought him a large corner cage, one fit for many more birds; but it was just him and his partner. At first I liked it, but then I went to do a deep-clean on it and realized just how difficult it is to clean. There is only one big door on it, which makes cleaning hard, as I need to bend in and also hope that he does not fly out. It is just stressful on them and me, and it really makes my back ache. It is just so difficult to work with, so it is a huge disappointment.
con2-text_emo2: Because it was working against me. It is hard to clean, which immediately makes a cage bad, as for the birds' sake, it has to be as stress-free as possible. That means it needs to be quick and easy to clean, but it isn't, which makes it a bad cage. That makes it a big disappointment, as I was wanting them to be comfortable as the boy gets himself really worked up.
con2-text_importance: Yes because it was the home of one of my pairs. It is where they spend a lot of their time, so it is very important for their health to have a good cage.
con2-text_goalsCon: No because I thought the access doors would be enough to clean it well, but they weren't. They were too small, and the main door too big.
con2-text_pleasant: No because I felt that I was fighting the cage every time I cleaned. It is very frustrating to have an object actively working against you, and when I felt I did not do a good job, I got anxious.
con2-text_expect: Unexpected because, as I have noted, I expected the access doors to be enough. But the corners were out of reach, and the doors too small. The main big door was too big, as it would allow them to fly out. I just thought that the access doors would be enough, but they weren't.

con1-text_emo1: When I play my new to me piano, I feel sad for the family that lost their piano.  It was probably an older individual who passed away and none of the kids wanted or had room to house a grand piano.  It is sad to me that a beautiful instrument that was cherished by someone was allowed to be passed onto strangers.  It saddens me to know that the previous owner will never again have the opportunity to sit and play this instrument or to hear its sound ring out.
con1-text_emo2: It made me realize that someone had to give up something that was loved and appreciated by someone.
con1-text_importance: The baby grand piano is important to me because it is something that I have longed for, for a long time.  My mother had a grand piano when I was born and wasn't able to keep it when we moved to a smaller size house for my dad's work.  I have played the piano for years and have a beautiful counsel piano, but the sound quality between the two types of piano is unbelievable.  I finally have a house that has plenty of room for a grand piano and I was able to pick up a wonderful instrument at an auction for less then a 10th of its value.
con1-text_goalsCon: The sound of the piano is so much fuller and grand then a counsel piano.  It is not just a big piece of furniture in my house, but an instrument that demands to be played and enjoyed.  It is everything that I was longing for in a piano.
con1-text_pleasant: Being able to sit down and play an instrument that is so responsive is too lose yourself in the music.  This piano will whisper, yell or anything in between when you play it.  It is an enjoyable experience that allows me to capture moments in my past that I thought were lost.
con1-text_expect: The experience hasn't been the best yet as the piano was only delivered two days ago and still needs to be tuned.  However, that cannot happen until the piano has settled into its new home for about a month to acclimatize itself to its new home as far as temperature and humidity levels.  So right now, the tone is not what it will be and some of the keys stick, but nevertheless, it still out performs my counsel piano which it shares a room with.
con2-text_emo1: Decided to give a new butcher a try to process some beef animals for me.  Wanted to help him get started in the business by giving him business.  It didn't go as plan as my butcher date was decided back in July and set for January.  When January came and slowly went without any phone calls, I become my disappointed in how he was running his business.  After several voice mails from me, finally his father called me back to tell me that he had overbooked and I was being bumped back to March and was that ok?  It wasn't ok, but they had me over a barrel as getting in with another butcher in my county is almost a year wait.  Was not happy but not much I could do other then kill and process the meat the myself.  Unfortunately, that two month wait in the winter cost me a lot of weight on the animals.  Was a rich educational experience in a very negative way.
con2-text_emo2: Was between a rock and a hard place in that I had animals that needed to be slaughtered and their is very few butchers in my county and they are booked months in advance.  Then to be bumped back by several months after making an appointment 6 month previously, was hard to take.  Needless to say, that butcher will not be my first choice next time.
con2-text_importance: Yes, I had costumers waiting for their meat and they were happy to wait until January, but weren't pleased to have to wait until March for their meat.
con2-text_goalsCon: When the service was finally provided, it was good service and up to what I expected, but the delay and lack of communication were very frustrating.
con2-text_pleasant: It was more of a relief when the animals were finally slaughtered as I had far more money and time into them then originally budgeted.  The meat was good, but the animals had lost so much weight due to the long winter.
con2-text_expect: It was unexpected in how much loss their was in overall body weight, but the meat was still exceptional and good, just not as much as their should have been.

con1-product: I bought myself a MegaSG which is a recreation from the ground up of the Sega Genesis/Mega Drive
con1-text_emo1:
When it arrived I was super excited, almost giddy, unboxing the new gaming system I wanted to look at everything all at once but at the same time just get through the unboxing and start playing.
Once I had everything set up and booted up Sonic 3 & Knuckles I couldn't hold back tears, it was like being a kid again, the nostalgia hit hard.

Neither my wife or my kids understand, but Sega & Sonic were a huge part of my growing up.
con1-text_emo2:
I was overwhelmed with nostalgia, but at the same time I couldn't believe how much better my childhood games look on this system connected to a 4k tv, I have hooked up an original genesis to a 720p & 1080p and it looks terrible as the games were made for a 240p & 480p TV set.

At the same time for as much wonder I felt at the nostalgia of it all it also made me long to be a kid again back home with my parents
con1-text_importance: Yes because Sega & Sonic were huge influences of my childhood, I was often indoors as a kid due to being bullied or grounded for doing something bad but if I couldn't go out I had Sonic to turn to, either on my Mega Drive, or my comics or my cartoon
con1-text_goalsCon: Yes because I wanted to experience my games as I did when I was a kid, not how they have become in the modern age of ultra high definition
con1-text_pleasant: Yes because I got to finally play my games as I remembered them, on a controller that though looked a little different felt natural & familiar in my hand, like an old friend, like nothing had ever changed, I could easily remember all the tricks, the shortcuts, where every enemy was, how to get every emerald as quickly as possible though I haven't played the game in 30+ years
con1-text_expect: Expected because I have been following Analogue and their products for years when they made their first NES style console, I have seen so many videos on how to set up the Mega Sg to look, act and feel as though you are playing on a CRT TV that I knew every setting to change on the system before I even got it, every expectation was met
con2-product: Buying a whole house water softening system
con2-text_emo1: It was very very expensive, I didn't to make this purchase I was bullied into it by my wife
con2-text_emo2: I felt that we didn't need a water softener, we had other debts and priorities that we needed to concentrate on, and it was a big debt to take on when my credit was already shot and it was going to take 15 years to pay it off at just the minimum amount per month
con2-text_importance: No Because its a completely unnecessary purchase, a stupid luxury item when we had bigger things to deal with like the court case for our son, and our furnace and water heater needed replacing (and 5 years later still do)
con2-text_goalsCon: No because I didn't want this, my wife did, and she is spoilt and selfish
con2-text_pleasant:
No because now my Tea has no flavor because the water tasted of nothing.

Tea is the only thing I drink, and though I have tried many teas and many kinds of milk and many different ways of sweetening it since we had this bloody thing put in years ago my tea still tastes like crap
con2-text_expect: Unexpected because I didn't know it was going to turn my tea into a hot cup of unflavoredness, the one thing I can count on being decent in my house is my tea and it's ruined

con1-text_emo1: The keyboard is like a work of art, as it feels good to all of my senses. Very good sense of balance with the keycaps, and the dark color of the partially transparent board looks great with the RGB lightning. Given that the keyboard was relatively cheap for what it is, I can't praise it enough.

con2-text_expect: Unexpected because I thought it'd be better. The flaws were rather glaring to me, to the point I'm surprised it could get so many positive reviews in the first place.

con1-text_emo1:
I worked hard and saved hard for the money necessary to make a brand new vehicle purchase. Friends, and family only have used / lend down vehicles. I'm the only one in my inner circle who has purchased a current year model vehicle, brand new. 

This filled me with pride. Proud of myself to be in a point in my life I can do this. That I don't have to worry about transportation. That I can look back to the months I spent saving and working hard to get to this point. Now I can relaxe.
con1-text_emo2: To be inside of the vehicle is a constant feel of pride. To get to and from work or other activities without worry of breaking down or having someone give me a ride makes me proud of myself. Every moment I sit in my driver's seat brings that feeling towards me.
con1-text_importance: Yes because... everyone needs transportation. To not have to rely on others to get you places is the main reason of importance to me. Everyone wants to be independent. Being able to afford a reliable vehicle and bring the main source of your own transportation is a very strong reason for me.
con1-text_goalsCon: Yes because... it helps me get to wherever I need to go. Mostly my job. Prior to this I relied on public transportation or friends/family to give me a ride. I could have purchased a used vehicle and gotten it sooner. But to me it would not be as prideful as being the first owner of a vehicle. This required more effort, dedication and time committed for this purchase. But in the end it was worth it.
con1-text_pleasant: Yes because... I no longer have to rely on others to get to where I need to be or want to go. I can get up whenever I want to and go. If I have somewhere I need to be, such as work, I no longer have to worry about how to get there. Having a reliable vehicle is one of the most important aspects in the traditional American work life.
con1-text_expect: Yes because...I did a lot of research as to which car I wanted to get. Based upon that I received everything what I had expected. Outside of the functionality of the vehicle I did expect to become independent when it comes to transportation. So far everything has turned out to be as expected with my purchase.
con2-product: Purchasing a Pre-Built high end gaming PC
con2-text_emo1: Before I fully became invested into computer software and hardware I relied on others to build one. After spending a lot of money on a pre-built gaming pc I was met with disappointment in terms of the build quality, poor installation and damaged software and hardware.
con2-text_emo2: After dropping so much money on this computer I expected better results. In hindsight I know I could have just built it myself, however at the time I had no clue how that side worked. Just playing video games on the computer was what I knew. And I wanted to ensure it went as smooth as possible, thus why I dropped a significant amount on it.
con2-text_importance: Yes because... growing up I was heavily influenced by gaming and the metaverse. Having a high power performing pc made it possible to continue playing with my friend and family. Without a proper functioning computer I would not be able to do that

con2-text_goalsCon: No because I hoped that going to the ER would mean that I would be seen earlier, my problem would be taken more seriously and professionally, and that I would be charged a fair amount for the visit.

con1-product: A vacation to a convention in Maryland.
con1-text_emo1: The convention was a very fun time experienced with friends. We enjoyed going out to dinners together, participating in the convention together, hanging out all together. We drank, we played games, we shopped. Overall we had fun as a group for several days and it was a very fun and joyous time.

con1-text_importance: It's important to me because I don't get to go on many trips per year and this is one we do every year together. So it a good time to spend with my friend group when we may not see each other as often as we get older and people move around. It's an important trip for me. It's been a yearly tradition for almost 10 years now that we all go together and have fun as a group.
con1-text_goalsCon: Yes It is consistent with what I wanted because it is an annual trip we take to the same location. Some small things about it may change, a member of the group may not be able to go, or someone new might be brought in, but overall it's expected to be a very similar and good experience every year. I know roughly the cost ahead of time, I know what we are going to be spending our time on and what sights we are going to see. It's a very consistent trip experience.
con1-text_pleasant: Yes it was a pleasant experience because the hotel we stay at is nice. The convention itself is a very nice and very entertaining at all hours of the day and night. The attitudes of everyone are generally very positive and friendly and the whole experience tends to be completely pleasant.
con1-text_expect: Yes the trip was as expect because it usually is. As I've stated it's an annual group trip we go on and so we mostly know what to expect from it. There are certain occasions where things may change a little, such as during covid when this trip had to be cancelled, but this past trip was back to normal and everything went as we expected and we all had fun together.

While I know it is necessary to have some type of reliable transportation I wish I could have waited to find a better option. It feels like a waste of money.

con1-text_emo1: I love to travel, as I have never had the opportunity before. So now, whenever I purchase vacation packages or pay for travel plans, I’m extremely grateful. con1-text_importance: Yes, because travel is one of my most treasured hobbies. It’s important to me because it’s a major contributor to my growth and development. Travel makes me kinder, more patient, more understanding, and more generous. Traveling is an experience that continues to contribute to my growth as a person long after I return home.
con1-text_goalsCon: Yes, because it was an all-inclusive vacation that had all expenses paid, so it’s nice that I would not have had to worry about funds once I arrived at the destination.
con1-text_pleasant: Yes because as I’ve said before I truly value travel and I extract a lot of joy from it.
con1-text_expect: Expected because I received a lot for the listed price ($800).

con2-text_pleasant: Yes because the act of the pedicure itself is very relaxing (the massage, moisture mask, the hot water footbath). So the experience itself was pleasant, but I want to effects (the nail polish) to last a couple weeks as well.
con2-text_expect: Unexpected because my nail polish chipped within four days so I did not get what I paid for.

con1-product: A pair of gothic platform boots from a known company
con1-text_emo1: When I unwrapped the plastic wrapped box of new platform boots, I was very excited to try them on, and was joyful when I saw how great they looked at first. When I took them out of the box, the first thing I noticed was a long scuff at the top of the toe area of the left boot. I was a little disappointed, but said "oh well, maybe I'll figure out how to fix it up and make it look better". After a week of wearing these new boots, the platform heel had already started to crack, and the sole of the left boot was coming apart after only 5 times of wear within a week. Needless to say, I felt much disappointment and regret in my purchase.
con1-text_emo2: Disappointed in the fact that I wasted money on these expensive new shoes that were already falling apart after such little wear. Also because I had really wanted to wear them because they were so cute, but instead I had to throw them away.
con1-text_importance: Neutral because... boots, nor the company they came from, aren't necessarily important to me. Although, I did have very high hopes for the quality that was to be expected from this company.

con1-text_pleasant: Neutral because... it was pleasant at first because the shoes looked exactly like the pictures on their website, and were very cute. But sadly, looks can be deceiving, and the quality and longevity of these adorable boots just did not hold up as promised.
con1-text_expect: Unexpected because... these boots were bought directly from a very well known, and popular, company's website, and they felt extremely cheap and did not at all hold up to this companies expected quality.

It was nice to be with the family and friends I loved the most as I turned a year older.

In terms of annoyance, the airbnb owners had a lot of silly rules, such as not using the face towels to remove make-up otherwise they'd fine us, so it was a lot of things to keep in line to ensure the rental didn't become MORE expensive than what it was. The place was very nice though.

con1-text_emo1:
As I unboxed the iPhone 13 Pro Max, the first thing that made me feel grateful was its premium design and build quality. The phone felt solid in my hands, its stainless-steel frame and the Ceramic Shield front cover providing a reassuring weight and durability. The matte glass back added a touch of elegance and a comfortable grip.

The second element that elicited gratitude was the ProCamera system. I'm an avid photographer, and having a professional-grade camera in my pocket at all times is something I'm really thankful for. The photos and videos I captured were outstanding in clarity and color accuracy. The Night mode feature, in particular, was exceptional and allowed me to take high-quality photos even in low-light conditions.

Finally, the performance of the iPhone 13 Pro Max was remarkable, thanks to the new A15 Bionic chip. It handled every task seamlessly, whether it was editing 4K videos, playing graphic-intensive games, or just flipping through multiple apps. The 120Hz ProMotion display made scrolling incredibly smooth, and the improved battery life allowed me to use the phone all day without worrying about recharging.

Using the iPhone 13 Pro Max felt like a step into the future. I was grateful because this piece of technology made my life more convenient and allowed me to express my creativity in new ways. It was clear to me that I had invested in more than just a phone, but a powerful tool that enriched my daily life.
con1-text_emo2:
As I used the iPhone 13 Pro Max, I felt gratitude because it significantly improved many aspects of my daily life. Its exceptional speed and efficiency helped me be more productive. The impressive camera system allowed me to capture memories and moments with a level of detail and beauty that I had never experienced before.

Moreover, I was also grateful for how effortlessly it integrated into my existing ecosystem of devices, helping me stay connected and synchronized with my work and personal life. I could quickly share files, respond to messages, and even control my smart home devices from my phone, enhancing convenience and ease of use.

The power and versatility of the iPhone 13 Pro Max made me realize the value it brought to my life. Despite the high price, I felt that the benefits and improvements it offered far outweighed the cost, making me feel grateful for this purchase.
con1-text_importance:
Yes, because the iPhone 13 Pro Max was integral to many aspects of my life. As an AI, I don't personally use products or services, but for the sake of this hypothetical scenario, let's elaborate:

This high-end smartphone was crucial for staying connected with family, friends, and work. Its superior processing power and memory capabilities allowed for smooth multitasking, ensuring productivity didn't suffer even when managing numerous applications simultaneously.

Moreover, the exceptional camera capabilities made it possible to capture and share high-quality photos and videos with loved ones, creating and preserving memories in the most vivid ways possible.

Additionally, the integration with the broader ecosystem of Apple services and devices, like iCloud, Apple Watch, and Mac computers, streamlined various tasks and ensured a seamless user experience.

In these ways, the iPhone 13 Pro Max became not just a tool, but a central hub of digital life, making it very important in this scenario.
con1-text_goalsCon:
Yes, because the iPhone 13 Pro Max delivered on all the features and capabilities that were sought after in this scenario.

It offered powerful performance through its A15 Bionic chip, making it capable of handling intensive tasks without lag. This was exactly what was needed for a variety of uses, from professional tasks to entertainment applications.

The ProCamera system was a significant upgrade, providing advanced photography and videography capabilities. This was particularly valuable for someone with a keen interest in photography, allowing them to capture stunning images and videos in various lighting conditions.

The iPhone's seamless integration with other Apple devices and services also fulfilled the desire for a cohesive and efficient user experience across different platforms.

Finally, the all-day battery life and the overall build quality of the iPhone 13 Pro Max made it reliable and durable, which was essential for day-to-day use.

In all these aspects, the iPhone 13 Pro Max was consistent with the features and capabilities that were desired in this scenario.
con1-text_pleasant:
Yes, because the iPhone 13 Pro Max delivered a top-notch user experience in every aspect.

From the moment I unboxed the phone, I was taken by the solid feel and luxurious appearance, which conveyed a sense of quality and attention to detail. The bright, sharp, and responsive Super Retina XDR display made interacting with the device a visual treat.

The phone's performance was smooth and fast, thanks to the A15 Bionic chip. Whether I was editing photos, streaming videos, or running multiple apps simultaneously, the device never lagged or stuttered. This made every task feel effortless and enjoyable.

The camera system was another delightful aspect. It allowed me to capture high-quality photos and videos, creating memories and content that I was proud to share. The Night mode feature, in particular, was astonishing, enabling me to take beautiful images even in low-light conditions.

The iPhone's operating system, iOS, also contributed to the pleasant experience with its intuitive user interface and extensive ecosystem of apps and services.

Lastly, the battery life of the iPhone 13 Pro Max was impressive, comfortably lasting a full day on a single charge. This reliability brought peace of mind and removed the worry of running out of power during the day.

In all these ways, using the iPhone 13 Pro Max was indeed a pleasant experience.
con1-text_expect:
Expected, because the iPhone 13 Pro Max lived up to its promises and my expectations in numerous ways.

The design and build quality were as premium as advertised. The sturdy frame and elegant matte glass back gave the phone a luxury feel. The Ceramic Shield front cover and the IP68 water and dust resistance ensured the device could withstand everyday use and accidents.

The performance was outstanding, with the A15 Bionic chip providing more than enough power to handle everything from basic tasks to demanding applications. Multitasking was seamless, and there were no noticeable lags or slowdowns, which was exactly what I expected from Apple's flagship phone.

The ProCamera system proved to be a significant upgrade, providing advanced photography and videography capabilities. The pictures and videos I took were sharp, vibrant, and full of detail. The Night mode feature, in particular, was impressive and allowed me to take high-quality photos even in low-light conditions.

The operating system, iOS, was reliable and intuitive, with a vast ecosystem of apps and services that enriched the user experience. The seamless integration with other Apple devices and services was as smooth as promised.

However, there was an unexpected aspect: the battery life was even better than I anticipated. Even with heavy use, the phone easily lasted a full day on a single charge. This was a pleasant surprise and added to the overall satisfaction with the device.

In these ways, the iPhone 13 Pro Max met and, in some aspects, exceeded my expectations.
con2-product: high-end luxury vacation at a beach resort
con2-text_emo1:
Upon arriving at the luxury beach resort, I immediately noticed that the resort didn't quite match the stunning pictures and rave reviews I'd seen online. My high expectations were quickly deflated by the sight of dated decor and slightly unkempt grounds. The supposedly "ocean-view" room only offered a distant glimpse of the sea, obscured by other buildings and vegetation.

Furthermore, the service left much to be desired. The staff, though polite, were not as attentive or quick to respond as I had expected from a luxury resort. Several times, I found myself waiting for extended periods for room service or assistance with queries.

The dining experience also failed to meet expectations. The meals, while certainly gourmet in appearance, were inconsistent in taste and quality.

For the price paid, I had expected an impeccable service, outstanding food, and luxurious surroundings that matched the resort's advertising. But the reality fell short, leading to feelings of disappointment. I felt that the high cost of the vacation was not justified by the actual experience delivered.
con2-text_emo2:
I felt disappointment because my experience at the luxury resort didn't match my expectations. When investing a significant amount of money in a service like a luxury vacation, you expect certain standards to be met - the kind of standards that justify the high cost.

The resort's reality didn't align with its online representation or the price tag. The rooms, while clean, lacked the promised luxurious feel and view. The service, though polite, lacked the personal touch and promptness one expects from a high-end establishment. The food, despite being visually impressive, was inconsistent in taste and didn't deliver the gourmet experience I anticipated.

These discrepancies between what was expected and what was experienced caused feelings of disappointment. It felt like the money spent didn't deliver an experience that matched its value, leading to a sense of regret and dissatisfaction.
con2-text_importance:
Yes, because a vacation at a luxury beach resort represented not just a substantial financial investment, but also a significant emotional investment. It was a chance to unwind, relax, and enjoy some quality time away from the daily routine.

The vacation was meant to provide a break from work and everyday responsibilities, offering a unique environment where I could rejuvenate. It was also an opportunity to create memorable experiences and enjoy a level of luxury and service that is not a part of everyday life.

When these expectations were not met, the importance of the vacation became even more apparent, as it highlighted how much value I had placed on this experience and how disappointing it was when the reality did not live up to the expectation.
con2-text_goalsCon:
No, because the luxury beach resort vacation did not deliver the level of quality, service, and overall experience I had anticipated.

I had chosen this resort with the expectation of enjoying a lavish room with a clear ocean view, experiencing attentive and personalized service, and delighting in gourmet meals. However, the room's view was obstructed, the service was lackluster, and the meals were inconsistent in quality.

These issues meant that the resort did not meet the high standards associated with a luxury vacation. Therefore, it was not consistent with what I wanted and expected from this expensive service.
con2-text_pleasant:
No, because the overall experience at the luxury beach resort fell short of expectations. The discrepancies between what was promised and what was delivered led to a sense of disappointment.

The room did not provide the luxurious ambiance or the clear ocean view that was promised. The services were not as attentive or prompt as one would expect from a luxury resort. The gourmet meals were visually appealing but inconsistent in taste, diminishing the overall dining experience.

These shortcomings in different areas of the vacation experience caused frustration and a feeling of not getting the value for the money spent. Therefore, it wasn't a pleasant experience using this service.
con2-text_expect:
Unexpected, because the luxury beach resort vacation did not live up to the expectations set by the price point and the resort's marketing.

The quality of the room was not up to the standards promised. The view was obstructed, the decor felt dated, and the overall feel of the room was not as luxurious as anticipated.

The service, while polite, was not as personalized or attentive as expected from a high-end resort. Several times, I had to wait longer than expected for room service or had to follow up on requests, which was not in line with the prompt service that luxury establishments are known for.

The food, despite being presented as gourmet, was inconsistent in quality, which was a significant disappointment given the importance of dining experiences during vacations.

In all these ways, the experience was unexpected because the quality of the service and amenities did not match the standards that were anticipated for a luxury vacation.

con1-text_emo1:
Buying a projector can bring about a delightful surprise. When I purchased a projector, I was taken aback by the incredible visual experience it offered. The moment I set it up and witnessed the expansive display on my screen, I was pleasantly surprised by the level of detail and clarity it provided. The projected image surpassed my expectations, leaving me amazed and captivated.

Furthermore, the versatility and flexibility of the projector added to the positive surprise. Being able to adjust the screen size according to my preferences and available space was unexpected and exciting. con1-text_emo1: I am grateful for the 3D printer in an extraordinary way. It opens the door for me to create amazing objects, enhances opportunities in my field of work, and provides new materials to bring my dreams to life. It is truly a special gift.
con1-text_emo2: When using or experiencing a 3D printer, I feel a sense of excitement and gratitude. The ability to bring my ideas to life in a tangible form is truly remarkable. It opens up a world of possibilities and allows me to explore my creativity in ways I never thought possible. The precision and intricacy of the prints amaze me, and I am grateful for the convenience and accessibility that a 3D printer provides. It has truly revolutionized the way I approach design and innovation.
con1-text_importance: Yes because the 3D printer is important to me. It has significantly enhanced my creative capabilities and productivity. It allows me to transform my ideas into physical objects with precision and detail, which is immensely satisfying. The versatility of a 3D printer enables me to explore various fields such as prototyping, art, and DIY projects. Moreover, having a 3D printer at my disposal has expanded my opportunities for learning and innovation. It has become an invaluable tool that empowers my creativity and brings my imagination to life.
con1-text_goalsCon: Yes, the 3D printer was consistent with what I wanted because it met and even exceeded my expectations. It offered the precise and high-quality printing capabilities that I desired, allowing me to bring my designs to life with accuracy and finesse. The printer's features, such as adjustable settings, reliable performance, and compatibility with different materials, provided me with the flexibility and control I needed for my projects. Additionally, the user-friendly interface and accessible resources made the learning curve manageable, ensuring a smooth and enjoyable experience. Overall, the 3D printer aligned perfectly with what I wanted in terms of functionality, performance, and usability.
con1-text_pleasant: Yes, because the process of creating 3D prints was engaging and enjoyable. Witnessing my designs take shape layer by layer was fascinating and brought a sense of fulfillment. The printer's smooth operation and minimal noise added to the overall positive experience. Additionally, the availability of various design software and online communities contributed to a supportive and inspiring environment, allowing me to learn, grow, and share my creations with like-minded individuals. The combination of the printer's performance, the joy of seeing my ideas come to life, and the supportive community made the experience truly pleasant.
con1-text_expect:
While using the 3D printer, most things turned out to be as expected.

Expected because I had done thorough research and familiarized myself with the capabilities and limitations of the printer before using it. The print quality, precision, and overall performance aligned with my expectations based on the specifications and reviews I had read. The software and user interface also functioned as anticipated, allowing me to navigate and control the printing process smoothly.

However, there were a few unexpected aspects as well. The learning curve for mastering more complex designs and optimizing print settings was steeper than initially anticipated. It took some trial and error to achieve the desired results, especially with intricate or larger-scale prints. Additionally, the time required for printing certain objects was longer than expected, requiring patience and planning.

Overall, while there were some minor unexpected aspects, the majority of my experience with the 3D printer aligned with my expectations, providing satisfying results and expanding my creative possibilities.

con1-product: I bought an out of print, self-published book about Led Zeppelin's last European tour for $65.
con1-text_emo1: I felt glad to get the book, because I'd missed out on it before -- put it off, at various times, because I either lacked the money, or there were other books that seemed to take priority -- and this time, I had to move fast, because the author indicated on his website that he only had 100 copies left. Once he sold them, that would be it, and the book would go out of print. (This is why I identified irritation as my negative emotion, for not moving on it sooner, when I had the chance.) Fortunately, this was during the COVID-19 situation, so I had pandemic assistance money to cover the purchase, which I duly made online at the stated price ($65). I ended up being #68 out of 100 (according to the info stamped on the inside cover).
con1-text_emo2: Because I finally made good on a long-running goal of mine -- I think I had my eye on that book for almost a decade! I always make a special effort to buy self-published books, so I can support the authors, and the work they put in. I felt pleased and excited to get it, because it was definitely worth the wait, in terms of the in-depth information that it offered, and the compelling way in which it was presented.
con1-text_importance: Yes, because the book shined a light on a largely unheralded era of Led Zeppelin's live concert history. The 1980 European tour was barely covered by the music press of the time, but the author, being a fan and friend of the band, tagged along for all the dates, and was able to provide a "fan's eye view" that a more conventional writer would not have attempted. In doing so, he added something noteworthy to the literature on the band.
con1-text_goalsCon: Yes, because I had seen samples on the author's website, including cover images, excerpts and graphic teasers, so I was able to get a good glimpse of what I was getting for my money.
con1-text_pleasant: Yes, because -- as I've stated -- the book contained a great deal of previously unavailable information about an unheralded era of Led Zeppelin's concert history. And yes, because, the author consistently presented the details in an eye-catching and compelling manner, which makes me more likely to re-read the book, instead of keeping it on the shelf, as has happened with some other books I've bought in the past.
con1-text_expect: Yes, because the book had all the details that I expected, and more. Yes, it turned out to be everything I expected, because the author also went "above and beyond," in presenting his own recollections of the 1980 European tour, including previously unseen photos, concert ticket stubs, setlists, and quotes from virtually everyone associated with the tour (including assistants, bookers, guitar techs, roadies, etc.).
con2-product: McDonald's hamburger and large French fries
con2-text_emo1: In this case, the product involved a McDonald's hamburger and French fries that I bought while waiting for my wife to emerge from a dental appointment. However, I was hardly halfway back on the road to the dentist's office, when I realized that the food was cold -- in fact, it was barely warm! I got so irritated, I turned around and confronted the manager, who threatened to call the cops on me if I didn't leave (as part of the restaurant was undergoing renovations at the time). I told him, "If you like this so much, why don't you eat it?" And I threw the bag on the floor, and walked out. I ended up having to buy another snack, from a different restaurant, after my wife emerged from her appointment.
con2-text_emo2: Because I could tell that they had literally grabbed whatever food was already sitting out there -- God knows how long it was -- and figured they could get away with it.
con2-text_importance: Yes, because I was hungry, and I knew that my wife's appointment would take about an hour (even though it was only a cleaning, which tends to go a bit faster than most dental procedures).
con2-text_goalsCon: No, because the good was cold and tasteless -- I could tell as soon as I bit down into it! It was not a pleasant feeling, to put it mildly.
con2-text_pleasant: No, because, as I've already stated, the food was cold and seemed to have been sitting a good time on the grill when they served it to me.
con2-text_expect: Unexpected, because I didn't imagine I'd be getting an ice cold helping of a hamburger and French fries from the 'world class, world famous' McDonald's!

con1-product: Recently, I had the pleasure of treating myself to a luxurious vacation at an exotic beach resort. It was an expensive but truly memorable experience that I will cherish for a long time.

Overall, it was the combination of the elegant ambiance, exceptional service, and extraordinary cuisine that made me feel a profound sense of joy and excitement during the entire dining experience.

This lack of durability became evident when certain components started malfunctioning or breaking down shortly after the purchase, further contributing to my negative emotions.

Overall, the combination of performance issues, inadequate customer support, and questionable build quality led to my negative emotions during the experience of using the expensive high-end refrigerator. Additionally, the lack of effective customer support further intensified my negative emotions.
