con1-product: A luxurious vacation to a tropical island destination
con1-text_emo1:
During my recent luxurious vacation, I chose the breathtaking destination of Bora Bora, a tropical paradise. I had the pleasure of staying in a private overwater bungalow at a luxurious resort, surrounded by stunning turquoise lagoons. Upon arrival, I was warmly greeted by the resort staff, who adorned me with fragrant flower leis and offered refreshing tropical drinks.

The surroundings of Bora Bora were absolutely captivating, with powdery white sand beaches, vibrant coral reefs, and majestic volcanic peaks that seemed to touch the clear blue sky. My accommodation experience was truly remarkable, as I stayed in a spacious overwater bungalow equipped with a plush king-sized bed, a glass-bottom floor for observing marine life, and a private deck providing direct access to the mesmerizing turquoise lagoon.

During my vacation, I had the opportunity to partake in a variety of unforgettable activities. I explored the colorful coral gardens while snorkeling, embarked on guided hikes to discover the island's natural wonders, and enjoyed a magical sunset cruise where playful dolphins accompanied our boat.

The culinary experiences were nothing short of exceptional. I delighted in exquisite dishes at the resort's fine dining restaurant, savoring the freshest seafood delicacies and indulging in mouthwatering desserts. To add a touch of romance, I also relished a candlelit dinner on the beach, serenaded by the gentle sound of the waves.

Pampering myself was a priority during this vacation, and the resort's spa provided the ultimate relaxation and rejuvenation. I treated myself to luxurious massages, soothing facials, and invigorating body scrubs, leaving me feeling completely renewed and pampered.

One of the most memorable moments of the trip was witnessing a breathtaking sunset from the private deck of my bungalow. The sky transformed into a stunning palette of oranges and pinks as the sun dipped below the horizon, creating a truly mesmerizing sight that will forever be etched in my memory.

Overall, this luxurious vacation in Bora Bora transported me to a dreamlike world of pure bliss and contentment. The tranquil surroundings, opulent accommodation, delectable dining experiences, and rejuvenating spa treatments combined to create an unforgettable escape into a realm of indulgence and luxury.During my recent luxurious vacation to the idyllic destination of Bora Bora, I immersed myself in the beauty and opulence of the tropical paradise. However, as I reflect on the experience, there are a few regrets that linger in my mind.

One regret I have is not fully exploring the cultural aspects of the island. While I indulged in the luxurious amenities and breathtaking surroundings, I missed out on the opportunity to engage with the local community, learn about their traditions, and immerse myself in their rich heritage. Looking back, I wish I had taken the time to connect with the local culture on a deeper level.

Another regret is not venturing beyond the resort's premises more often. While the resort offered an array of activities and experiences, I realize now that I may have missed out on discovering hidden gems and unique attractions beyond the confines of the resort. Exploring the island further would have provided a more comprehensive understanding of Bora Bora's natural wonders and local life.

Additionally, I regret not capturing more moments through photography. The stunning vistas, vibrant marine life, and breathtaking sunsets deserved to be captured and cherished. I wish I had taken the time to document these incredible sights, allowing me to relive the memories and share the beauty of the destination with others.

Lastly, there is a sense of regret for not fully disconnecting from the outside world during my vacation. While the intention was to escape the daily routine and immerse myself in relaxation, I found myself occasionally checking emails and staying connected to work-related matters. In hindsight, I wish I had embraced the opportunity to disconnect completely, allowing myself to fully unwind and recharge without any distractions.

Despite these regrets, I still cherish the overall experience of the luxurious vacation in Bora Bora. It served as a reminder to seize every opportunity, embrace new experiences, and prioritize immersion in local culture. These regrets have taught me valuable lessons for future travels, encouraging me to seek a more balanced and mindful approach to exploring new destinations.
con1-text_emo2:
The emotions I experienced while using or experiencing a product or service can be attributed to a variety of factors. Here are some potential reasons why I felt those specific emotions:

Personal Expectations: My emotions were influenced by the expectations I had for the product or service. When my expectations were met or exceeded, I felt a sense of joy, satisfaction, or excitement. Conversely, if my expectations were not met, I might have felt disappointed or frustrated.

Perceived Value: The emotions I felt were closely tied to how I perceived the value of the product or service. If I believed that it provided significant value in relation to its cost or effort, I experienced positive emotions such as happiness or contentment. However, if I felt that the value was lacking, I might have felt regret or dissatisfaction.

Quality and Performance: The emotions I experienced were directly influenced by the quality and performance of the product or service. When it surpassed my expectations in terms of functionality, durability, or effectiveness, I felt a sense of delight or admiration. However, encountering issues with the quality or performance triggered emotions of frustration or disappointment.

Personal Relevance: The emotions I felt were also tied to how personally relevant the product or service was to my needs, desires, or aspirations. When it perfectly aligned with my preferences and goals, I felt a strong connection or fulfillment. However, if it did not resonate with my personal values or desires, I experienced a sense of dissonance or disconnect.

Context and Surroundings: The emotions I felt were influenced by the context and surroundings in which I used or experienced the product or service. For instance, if I was in a pleasant environment, surrounded by supportive people, or engaged in a special occasion, my emotions were enhanced positively. Conversely, negative or stressful contexts could have influenced negative emotions.

con2-product: a luxurious vacation to a tropical island destination
con2-text_emo1:
During my recent adventure-seeking expedition, I embarked on a thrilling journey to the rugged landscapes of Patagonia, a haven for outdoor enthusiasts. This vast and untamed region, known for its dramatic mountains, pristine lakes, and sprawling glaciers, became the perfect setting for my adrenaline-fueled escapades.

I began my expedition by conquering the mighty peaks of the Andes. With my trusted climbing gear, I embarked on a challenging ascent, navigating through rocky terrains and icy slopes. The sheer exhilaration of reaching the summit, surrounded by panoramic views of snow-capped peaks and sprawling valleys, filled me with a sense of accomplishment and awe.

Exploring the expansive wilderness of Patagonia, I ventured on epic hiking trails that led me deep into its untamed heart. Trekking through lush forests, crossing gushing rivers, and traversing remote valleys, I felt a profound connection to nature and a profound sense of freedom. The raw beauty of the landscapes, with its towering granite walls and cascading waterfalls, left me in awe at every turn.

To immerse myself in the true spirit of Patagonia, I embarked on a thrilling kayaking adventure. Gliding through crystal-clear lakes, surrounded by towering mountains, I felt a rush of adrenaline as I navigated through swirling rapids and gentle currents. The sheer serenity of the untouched wilderness around me was both humbling and invigorating.

In search of a truly unique experience, I decided to challenge myself with ice climbing on the majestic glaciers of Patagonia. Equipped with crampons and ice axes, I scaled the shimmering walls of ancient ice formations. The sheer power and beauty of these glaciers, with their deep crevasses and icy blue hues, left me in awe of nature's wonders.

As the sun set over the rugged Patagonian landscape, I found solace in the warmth and comfort of a cozy mountain lodge. Nestled amidst the wilderness, with breathtaking views of the surrounding peaks, it became a sanctuary where I could reflect on the day's adventures and connect with fellow travelers who shared the same passion for exploration.

Throughout my journey in Patagonia, I was constantly reminded of the raw power and unyielding beauty of nature. The exhilaration of conquering challenging landscapes, the serenity of untouched wilderness, and the camaraderie forged with fellow adventurers created an unforgettable experience that will forever be etched in my memory.

In the heart of Patagonia, I discovered a world where thrill and tranquility coexist, where nature's grandeur unfolds at every step, and where the spirit of adventure knows no bounds. This expedition not only tested my physical limits but also awakened a deep appreciation for the untamed beauty of our planet and the indomitable spirit that lies within us all.

con1-product: This is a good experience. There was a GPU shortage in 2021-2022 and I bought a GPU from EVGA. They had a queue where you could sign up and it allowed to me to be able to purchase said graphics processing unit in a time where bots and scalpers would scoop everything up. This was out of the ordinary for a graphics card manufacturer to do. Then again that company has the best customer service in the business. When your name came up in the queue they emailed you with a link to purchase. Was the best solution possible to get graphics cards into the hands of people who wanted them with no middleman.
con1-text_emo1: Getting said product for msrp when you could not get one anywhere. Being able to partake in a hobby I love which is computers. Being able to play games how they were intended to be played. My old graphics card was outdated.
con1-text_emo2: I guess it was like winning a game or lotto of some sort if we are talking about in that particular moment.
con1-text_importance: Yes because I enjoy playing video games. I have ever since I was a kid and got my first Nintendo Entertainment System. I also love building and modding my personal computer.
con1-text_goalsCon: It was consistent with what I wanted because it showed how much the company cares about its customers. Service that was above and beyond what a company normally does. I have such a fondness for that company. Probably the best customer service you can get of any company.
con1-text_pleasant: Yes because I was able to buy and use the product in a time where you could not. The actual process to buy was a little archaic but it worked. So I guess the buying process was a little lackluster but it got the job done.
con1-text_expect: Yes the buying process and the product are exactly as described by the company and reviewers of the performance of the product. The unexpected part was learning to install it I guess but that was my first experience with watercooling and nothing on the product or company.

con1-product: I bought a luxury wristwatch by Bulova from the eBay website.
con1-text_emo1: It made me feel proud to own this wristwatch because it was shiny and beautiful. This Bulova watch in all its glory before I ruined it by being clumsy was quite beautiful. It still has all the Swarovski crystals on the bezel and the mother of pearl face is luminous. Also, the stainless steel has yet to tarnish. Just, I broke it and I must have it fixed in that it needs a battery and it needs the window for the date repaired. It was gorgeous when I first had it though; greatly coveted by this one female friend I remember who is now gone.
con1-text_emo2: I was feeling that emotion because I simply loved looking upon the beauty of the watch itself.
con1-text_importance: At the time, yes, no pun intended. Of course it is important to know what time it is and a watch is a most excellent tool for discerning such.
con1-text_goalsCon: At first it was but after it degenerated so quickly into disrepair, I feel perhaps it is a convincing replica and not a true Bulova ladies wristwatch. I could be mistaken, but, since I could not find the exact model number matching its photo online, also, I think I got the ol' shim-shaft. I should have known also because ninety-one dollars is too inexpensive for a genuine Belova watch and you get what you pay for. I paid ninety-one dollars so I got a replica, I gather. I don't know but I definitely suspect. It is humorous and ironic to me still at almost forty years of age that hindsight is always 20/20.
con1-text_pleasant: Yes it was pleasant to look at my watch. Even though it doesn't function properly, it is still pleasing to look at. It is just dysfunctional in that the time it does not tell until I repair it.
con1-text_expect: It turned out unexpected because like I said I was easy on it when I cleaned it and it fell into disrepair unexpectedly and rapidly for what it was supposed to be.
con2-product: My Smok mod is really great and it didn't disappoint me like the Bulova watch.
con2-text_emo1: It works so well and I love everything about it. It is the Smok mod the Magnum one that resembles a pistol grip. I bought it because the thing is indestructible! It is even waterproof and shockproof in case I do something clumsy (again).
con2-text_emo2: I was feeling pride and joy because the thing just performs so well at smoking nicotine vapor. I really love it. I am out of vape juice right now, but, as soon as I get some I am utilizing it because it is fun.
con2-text_importance: No, not really, Water is important. Food is important. This is just a silly luxury item!

con2-text_pleasant: It was a pleasant experience because it is the monster truck of mods. The tank is huge so you don't have to refill it all the time and it just has some good vaping power.
con2-text_expect: Yes and better because the product outdid the hype and is as good or better than they say.

con1-text_emo1:
During my recent escapade, I embarked on an exhilarating adventure to the enchanting city of Kyoto, Japan, known for its rich cultural heritage and breathtaking landscapes. I had the pleasure of staying in a traditional Japanese ryokan, nestled amidst serene gardens and adorned with elegant tatami mats and sliding paper doors. As I entered the ryokan, I was greeted by the warm smiles of the staff and the soothing fragrance of freshly brewed green tea.

The city of Kyoto unfolded before me like a living canvas, with its majestic temples, vibrant cherry blossom trees, and serene bamboo forests. Exploring the iconic Kinkaku-ji, also known as the Golden Pavilion, was a surreal experience as the golden structure shimmered under the gentle rays of the sun. Walking through the Arashiyama Bamboo Grove, I felt a sense of tranquility envelop me as the towering bamboo stalks swayed gracefully in the breeze, creating a mesmerizing symphony of nature.

Every meal in Kyoto was a culinary delight, offering a glimpse into the traditional flavors and artistry of Japanese cuisine. I relished the delicate flavors of sushi and sashimi, indulged in hearty bowls of ramen, and delighted in the intricate beauty of kaiseki, a multi-course meal that showcased the skillful presentation of seasonal ingredients. Each bite was a harmonious blend of flavors and textures that left me craving for more.

Immersing myself in the tranquil beauty of Kyoto, I participated in a traditional tea ceremony, where I learned about the intricate rituals and serene mindfulness that accompanies the art of tea preparation. The meditative experience allowed me to appreciate the simplicity and grace of Japanese culture.

To capture the essence of Kyoto, I visited the famed Fushimi Inari Shrine, known for its stunning trail of thousands of vermilion torii gates. Walking through the gates, I felt a sense of spiritual connection and awe as I ventured deeper into the mystical forest, surrounded by a hushed ambiance and the gentle rustling of leaves.

As the day drew to a close, I sought solace in the peaceful embrace of an onsen, a traditional Japanese hot spring bath. The soothing thermal waters rejuvenated my body and soul, washing away the fatigue of the day and leaving me with a profound sense of relaxation.

My time in Kyoto was a tapestry of unforgettable moments, where ancient traditions met modern marvels, and natural beauty intertwined with cultural treasures. The city's timeless charm, coupled with its warm hospitality and captivating experiences, created a journey of discovery and enchantment that will forever hold a special place in my heart.
con1-text_emo2:
During my luxurious vacation in Kyoto, I experienced a range of emotions, from awe and fascination to tranquility and contentment. Each aspect of the trip contributed to these emotions in different ways.

Staying in a traditional Japanese ryokan immersed me in the rich cultural heritage of Kyoto, evoking a sense of awe and fascination. The elegant tatami mats, sliding paper doors, and the warm hospitality of the staff created an atmosphere of authenticity and tranquility, making me feel connected to the traditional Japanese way of life.

Exploring the majestic temples, vibrant cherry blossom trees, and serene bamboo forests of Kyoto filled me with a sense of wonder and appreciation for the beauty of nature and the rich history of the city. The golden shimmer of Kinkaku-ji, the swaying bamboo stalks in Arashiyama, and the tranquility of Fushimi Inari Shrine all evoked emotions of awe and a deep reverence for the beauty surrounding me.

The culinary experiences in Kyoto were a delight to the senses, with each dish meticulously prepared and presented. The delicate flavors, harmonious combinations, and the artistry of Japanese cuisine evoked a sense of pleasure and satisfaction, leaving me with a feeling of culinary bliss.

Participating in a traditional tea ceremony brought a sense of tranquility and mindfulness. The focus on the intricate rituals and the serene ambiance created an environment where I could fully immerse myself in the moment, leaving me feeling centered and at peace.

Indulging in the thermal waters of an onsen provided a profound sense of relaxation and rejuvenation. The soothing properties of the hot springs melted away the tension in my body and allowed me to unwind, leading to a feeling of deep contentment and tranquility.

Overall, each experience in Kyoto evoked different emotions, from awe and fascination to tranquility and contentment. The combination of cultural immersion, natural beauty, culinary delights, and moments of relaxation created a tapestry of emotions that made my time in Kyoto truly memorable.

con2-text_emo1:
During the recent past, I treated myself to an unforgettable experience by indulging in a lavish spa retreat. I decided to escape the hectic pace of my everyday life and immerse myself in a weekend of pure relaxation and self-care at a luxurious wellness resort nestled in a peaceful countryside setting.

As I arrived at the resort, I was immediately greeted by the serene ambiance of trickling water from a nearby fountain and the delightful aroma of essential oils in the air. The tranquil atmosphere instantly put my mind at ease, setting the perfect backdrop for the serene experience that awaited me.

I was escorted to my own private suite, a sanctuary of tranquility and comfort. The room was beautifully adorned with soothing colors, plush furnishings, and soft, ambient lighting. The inviting bed beckoned me to unwind and enjoy a restful night's sleep.

The next morning, my spa journey began with a heavenly full-body massage. The skilled hands of the therapist worked their magic, relieving tension and inducing a state of pure relaxation. The aromatic oils used during the massage enveloped my senses, transporting me to a place of deep serenity.

Throughout the day, I had the pleasure of experiencing a range of rejuvenating treatments. From indulgent facials that left my skin radiant to invigorating body scrubs that revitalized my senses, each treatment was tailored to provide a luxurious and personalized experience.

In between spa sessions, I took full advantage of the resort's exceptional amenities, such as the heated pool and jacuzzi. The warm waters embraced my body, melting away any lingering stress and tension. I also found solace in the serene gardens, where I could meditate and reconnect with the soothing power of nature.

Mealtimes at the resort were an absolute delight for my taste buds. The talented chefs crafted gourmet dishes using the freshest locally sourced ingredients. Each plate was a culinary masterpiece, meticulously presented and bursting with flavors that tantalized my palate. The combination of nourishing and delicious cuisine provided a harmonious complement to my overall wellness experience.

As the weekend drew to a close, I couldn't help but feel a profound sense of rejuvenation and renewal. The spa retreat had offered me a much-needed escape from the demands of my daily life, allowing me to prioritize my own well-being and self-care. I emerged from the experience feeling refreshed, recharged, and ready to face the world with a renewed sense of balance and inner peace.

This spa retreat was more than just a luxurious indulgence; it was a valuable investment in my physical, mental, and emotional well-being. It served as a gentle reminder of the importance of carving out dedicated time for myself, nurturing my body and soul, and finding moments of serenity amidst the hustle and bustle of life."

It ended up being much larger and heavier than expected, so it takes up a ton of room and I can't move it on my own. It was a lot of money for something that does a mediocre job (I do bookbinding and have to cut text blocks and dust coveres). I know a different product I would have much rather had.
con2-text_emo2: As I said before, I know now of  a product that I would much rather have. But it is difficult to justify purchasing another expensive guillotine when I already have one (mediocre as it is).
con2-text_importance: Yes because I need it for my bookbinding hobby. Accuracy/the ability to cut consistent measurements are two very important aspects to a guillotine for me. Unfortunately, I've struggled to get either out of this product.
con2-text_goalsCon: No because while it is the correct type of guillotine, having a press to hold down large textblocks while I make cuts, the difficulty with cutting straight lines and making precise measurements/cuts consistently make it very frustrating to use and own.
con2-text_pleasant: No because I have ended up with many textblocks/dust covers that are cut crooked. It is very frustrating to mess things up at that stage of creation. Textblocks take many hours to put together, and dust covers I have to drive to a local printshop to pickup.
con2-text_expect: Unexpected because I did not foresee the issues cutting straight (some part must be misaligned). I also didn't think about how it doesn't have a great system for measuring what you are cutting, so my books end up different sizes.

It also had a large screen and a loud fan, which made it conspicuous and noisy in public places. I felt that the laptop was not very portable or convenient for traveling or working outside. I wished that it was more compact and lightweight.
con1-text_importance: Yes, because the laptop was important to me for several reasons. First, it was a significant investment that I made with my own money, and I wanted to get the best value and quality for it. Second, it was a tool that I needed for my work and personal projects, and I wanted to have a reliable and efficient device that could support my goals and interests. Third, it was a source of entertainment and enjoyment for me, and I wanted to have a fun and satisfying experience with it. On the one hand, the laptop was consistent with what I wanted in terms of its performance and features. It had a powerful processor, a large memory, a high-resolution screen, a good keyboard, a clear sound system, and a durable design. It also had some extra features that I liked, such as a fingerprint scanner, a webcam cover, and a backlit keyboard. These aspects of the laptop matched what I wanted and needed for my work and entertainment purposes. On the other hand, the laptop was not consistent with what I wanted in terms of its portability and convenience. It was heavy and bulky, making it difficult to carry around or fit in my bag. I enjoyed working on my projects, browsing the internet, watching videos, playing games, and listening to music with my laptop. The laptop was fast, smooth, and responsive, and it did not give me any problems or errors. I felt satisfied and happy with the laptop’s performance and features. On the other hand, it was not a pleasant experience when I was using the laptop outside or in a crowded and noisy place. I felt annoyed and embarrassed by the laptop’s weight and size, and it caused me some inconvenience and discomfort. The laptop was hard to carry around or fit in my bag, and it attracted unwanted attention and noise. I felt dissatisfied and unhappy with the laptop’s portability and convenience. Therefore, it was a mixed experience when I was using the laptop, depending on the context and environment.

Some things turned out to be expected, and some things turned out to be unexpected. Here are some examples:

Expected because I had done some research and comparison before buying the laptop. I knew what kind of specifications and features it had, and I had read some reviews and feedback from other users. I also had seen and tested the laptop in the store before making the purchase. Therefore, I had a clear idea of what to expect from the laptop in terms of its performance and quality.

Unexpected because I had not considered the importance of portability and convenience for my lifestyle and needs. I had focused more on the technical aspects of the laptop, and I had overlooked the practical aspects of using it. I also had not realized how heavy and bulky the laptop was until I tried to carry it around or fit it in my bag. con1-text_emo1: I bought a 5.4cf washing machine without an agitator.  I thought it would be great for washing blankets and large items like cat bedding etc.  However, you had little to no control over the amount of water that was put in the tub and blankets can be light, but take up a lot of room and the tub would only have about six inches of water at the bottom.  Without an agitator and no control over the amount of water, the larger items did not get properly washed.  It was very disappointing.  Some items had to be washed multiple times and still were not as clean as I would have hoped.  Extremely disappointing and will never buy a washing machine that I cannot control the water levels on again or without an agitator.
con1-text_emo2: I felt disappointed because the washing machine did not clean the larger items such as blankets and cat bedding anywhere near good enough.  I had no control over the water level of the machine because it would decide based on weight how much water was needed and blankets can weigh little, but take up a lot of space and actually need a larger amount of water.  The machine would not let you adjust for that and items did not come out clean enough.  I will never buy a washing machine that does let you control water levels again.
con1-text_importance: Yes, because I needed the laundry to come out clean.  I have pets and sometimes have soiled blankets / bedding that needs to be washed and I want them to come out clean.  I had to wash the items multiple times and it still was unsatisfactory.
con1-text_goalsCon: Yes, because I needed a washing machine, but buying a washing machine where I could not control water levels and it was done for you by the machine was an extremely bad choice.
con1-text_pleasant: No, because it did not wash the items well enough.  I had to use a lot more bleach than should have been necessary and I still wasn't happy with the final wash.
con1-text_expect: Unexpected, because I had bought a high quality Maytag washing machine that had a sanitizing cycle and I thought that I would have clean laundry and with a big tub be able to do a lot of laundry at once, but the machine controlled the water level and it did a lousy job of cleaning the laundry satisfactorily.
con2-text_emo1: I bought an exercise bike which allows me to exercise at home.  I am very sensitive to the heat and I can aim a large fan in my direction while I use the exercise bike and I like using the bike at home.
con2-text_emo2: I am grateful to be able to look after my health in my own home rather than having to go out in the sun to get my exercise.  I don't like the heat or the sun.

con2-text_goalsCon: Yes, because using an exercise bike is easier on my arthritis and allows me to get my cardio without inflicting pain on my joints.
con2-text_pleasant: Yes, because I know that I am doing something good for myself and my health.
con2-text_expect: Yes, it turned out as expected, even better than expected because the customer service for the bike was better than I expected.  However, I also get to do my exercise at home while watching television and having a fan aimed at myself to keep me from overheating and it makes the experience more pleasant.

con1-product: A bed fram for my son.
con1-text_emo1: I was so disappointed in this purchase. It was such a waste of money. It was so difficult to put together, and the parts looked pretty cheap for such an expensive bed frame with great reviews. My son got maybe 4 months of use out of it before the slats started cracking. 5 months in and one night, he was sleeping, and it completely collapsed in on him. The slates all split down the middle, and the shift caused the legs on the foot of the bed to crack and break. What a waste.
con1-text_emo2: I was very frustrated at the poor quality of the materials. I was disappointed and angry and didn't feel like going through the hassle of having to argue with customer service over their crappy products and warranties. I am upset that my son is n a mattress on the floor while I have to save up for another frame, and this all happens right as every other expensive thing I own is failing or needs replacing.
con1-text_importance: Yes because I want my son to be comfortable in his room and for him to like the way it looks. I want him to be proud of his space.
con1-text_goalsCon: No because for the amount that I paid for it, I expected it to last for several years. I wanted quality. I expected better since the reviews were so good.
con1-text_pleasant: Neutral because it was great before it broke. My son loved the headboard and said it was comfortable with his mattress. But when it cracked and broke, it became unuseable
con1-text_expect: Unexpected because of the price, good reviews, and how it had held up just fine until one night he was sleeping.
con2-text_emo1: Back in 2011, I saved for months to buy my very first Macbook. I had wanted one for so long, and I finally did it.One of the best purchases I ever made. It was fast, smooth, and everything I was looking for. I called her Bessie. Bessie lasted me almost 14 years. She just pooped out on me 2 weeks ago. Now I'm saving for a new one. But Bessie helped me the most this past year when I got accepted to Prolific and found sites like Cloud Research and PaidViewPoint. It has helped me stay afloat because I am no longer able to work.
con2-text_emo2: I have always been somewhat of a tech nerd, so buying new laptops and expensive electronics is always exciting to me. They help me get work done, and help me relax by gaming or streaming afterward.
con2-text_importance: The Macbook was important to me because it helped me get work done. Homework, resumes, access to the internet on a screen larger than a phone for once, and was just useful overall for over a decade. RIP Bessie.
con2-text_goalsCon: Yes because, at the time of purchase, it was the latest and greatest. It had the latest operating system, I was able to play Steam games, and helped me with a lot of my work from home/data entry jobs as a second screen.
con2-text_pleasant: Yes because I enjoy surfing the web, finding new products, and having access to all of the information in the world right at my fingertips, as cliche as that may sound.
con2-text_expect: Everything was better than expected. It was my first Macbook experience. Currently saving for another!

con1-text_emo1: The products (used together, as part of a beauty regimen) made my skin oily, and I saw no obvious clarifying results. The products were of quality ingredients and certainly made my face feel softer, but the amount of time it took to layer each item on made it impossible for me to do it every day. Additionally, a couple of the products are so thick that the entire regimen as a whole is best to do during the winter months when my skin is the driest. I feel ridiculous looking at hundreds of dollars worth of products I can't use except for 2-3 months out of the year.
con1-text_emo2: The items are so expensive that I could've bought 20 serum ampoules and moisturizer tubes from a brand that's significantly cheaper and gave me noticeably remarkable results from the very first time I used them. Obviously, I wish I'd simply stocked up on the cheaper stuff instead.
con1-text_importance: Yes because I was expecting spectacular results from the price and excellent reputation that the brand has had for almost a century. I'm sure they probably do have some wonderful products, but I can't bring myself to try anymore because of this one mistake.
con1-text_goalsCon: No because I couldn't see noticeable results after multiple uses, whereas a much cheaper brand brightened  and smoothed my skin better than I ever would've imagined after the very first use.
con1-text_pleasant: Yes because while a bit thicker than I would've preferred, the products did offer a soothing, protective feel. Plus, while applying it, it did feel pretty luxurious because I felt like I was doing something nice for myself.
con1-text_expect: Unexpected because I expected a noticeable difference to my complexion, which I never saw even after multiple uses.
con2-product: I decided to try some makeup products from a famous designer British brand, and though I can't splurge much at one time because of the prices, every single item I've tried makes my skin look incredible!
con2-text_emo1: I wanted to try this brand's makeup products because many of their items are made to be applied in multiple areas -- lip tints work great as blushers, for example. I thought that was really cool and considerate for potential clients who want quality products but have a stricter budget. When I received the lip/cheek color, I was incredibly impressed by the texture of the product -- light a creamy for a discernable glow on the cheeks, yet light enough that it could work as a barely there lip tint or dark, dramatic pop of color. Not only was it made to be used as a double product, but each layer you add makes it practically a different color/shade. So many products in one... as a shopper who doesn't have the financial means to buy whatever I want whenever I like, I felt like the brand in total acknowledged and valued people like me as customers. That meant -- and still means -- the world to me.
con2-text_emo2: I felt seen, heard, and respected by the brand despite not having the finances of their usual upscale clientele. It makes me feel that this company wants everyone to feel beautiful in their own skin, regardless of socioeconomic factors. con2-product: I recall purchasing an expensive home security system that I had high hopes for.
con2-text_emo1:
The home security system I purchased ended up causing frustration and disappointment, leading to a negative emotional experience.

Initially, I was drawn to the product due to its advanced features and promises of enhanced security. However, the reality of using the system fell short of my expectations. The installation process was complex and time-consuming, requiring technical expertise that I didn't possess. It was frustrating to navigate through the instruction manual and troubleshoot various issues that arose during the setup.

Once installed, the system's performance proved to be unreliable. The surveillance cameras often experienced connectivity issues, resulting in intermittent video feeds and missed recordings. The motion sensors were overly sensitive, triggering false alarms frequently, which not only disrupted my peace but also strained the patience of my family members and neighbors.

The mobile app, which was supposed to provide convenient access and control, was riddled with bugs and glitches. It often crashed or failed to respond, rendering it useless when I needed to monitor my home remotely. The customer support from the company was unresponsive and unhelpful, adding to my frustration and sense of disappointment.

The overall experience of using the expensive home security system was marred by technical difficulties, unreliability, and poor customer support. Instead of feeling secure and protected, I felt let down and regretful about investing a significant amount of money in a product that failed to deliver on its promises. The negative emotions that arose from this experience were rooted in the product's inability to meet my expectations and provide the sense of security it had initially promised.
con2-text_emo2:
I was feeling frustrated and disappointed when using the home security system due to a combination of factors.

Firstly, the complex installation process and lack of clear instructions caused confusion and increased my frustration. I had expected a user-friendly setup, but instead, I found myself struggling to understand the technicalities and troubleshoot issues that arose.

Secondly, the system's unreliable performance and frequent connectivity problems undermined its effectiveness. The cameras' intermittent video feeds and missed recordings left me questioning the system's reliability and effectiveness in providing adequate security for my home. The constant false alarms triggered by the overly sensitive motion sensors not only disrupted my peace but also eroded my confidence in the system's functionality.

The mobile app's unreliability added to my frustration. The crashes, unresponsiveness, and inability to access the system remotely when needed made me question the value of the investment I had made. Instead of feeling empowered and in control, I felt limited and hindered by the product's technical shortcomings.

Lastly, the lack of responsive customer support compounded my negative emotions. The unresponsiveness and unhelpfulness of the company's support team left me feeling unheard and unsupported, exacerbating my disappointment and disillusionment.

Overall, the combination of complex installation, unreliable performance, technical glitches, and unhelpful customer support contributed to my negative emotions while using the home security system. It failed to meet my expectations, leaving me frustrated and disappointed with the product's performance and overall experience.
con2-text_importance: The security and safety of my home and loved ones are paramount to me. I wanted to invest in a reliable and effective home security system to provide peace of mind and protection against potential intruders or threats. The product's promises of advanced surveillance, motion sensors, and remote monitoring appealed to my desire for a comprehensive security solution. Protecting my home and creating a safe environment for my family was a top priority, making the product's importance evident to me.
con2-text_goalsCon: I had expected the home security system to provide reliable and effective surveillance, motion detection, and remote monitoring capabilities. However, the system fell short of these expectations. The frequent connectivity issues, unreliable performance, and false alarms indicated that the product was not consistent with what I had envisioned. The technical glitches and lack of responsiveness from the mobile app further added to the inconsistency, hindering my ability to effectively monitor and control the system. Overall, the product's performance and functionality did not align with what I wanted and expected from a high-end home security system.
con2-text_pleasant:
No, because it was not a pleasant experience when using the home security system.

The frustrations and disappointments I encountered during the installation process, the system's unreliable performance, and the technical glitches with the mobile app contributed to a lack of enjoyment and satisfaction. Instead of feeling a sense of reassurance and peace of mind, I was constantly dealing with connectivity issues, missed recordings, and false alarms, which created more stress and anxiety. The overall experience of using the product was marred by frustration, disappointment, and a lack of reliability, making it far from a pleasant experience.
con2-text_expect:
Everything turned out to be unexpected when using the home security system.

I had expected a seamless and user-friendly installation process, but instead, I encountered complexities and confusion that were unexpected. The lack of clear instructions and the technical challenges during setup were far from what I had anticipated.

The system's unreliable performance and frequent connectivity issues were also unexpected. I had hoped for consistent surveillance, accurate motion detection, and reliable remote monitoring, but instead, I experienced intermittent video feeds, missed recordings, and false alarms. These unexpected issues undermined the system's effectiveness and left me questioning its reliability.

Additionally, the technical glitches with the mobile app were unexpected. I had expected a smooth and responsive interface, but instead, I encountered crashes, unresponsiveness, and an inability to access the system remotely. These unexpected technical difficulties further hampered my overall experience with the product.

Overall, the home security system failed to meet my expectations, and the unexpected challenges and issues I encountered during its use were far from what I had anticipated.

I was at risk for getting into an accident and simply just driving fast or for a longer distance would give me anxiety. I thought about all of that as I got my tires changed and feeling anxiety free and safe while I drive is going be a great change for me.
con1-text_emo2: I was feeling that way because I have been driving around on old tires for a long time, and I was at risk for having one of the tires pop at any given time while in use, which would lead to some dangerous outcomes. Getting rid of that burden made me feel optimistic.

con1-text_goalsCon: Yes because now I have new wheels and I don't have to worry about changing them or having one explode on me causing an accident, which is a major relief.
con1-text_pleasant: Neutral because the service was more or less a means to an end. The end result, post service, made it a pleasant experience
con1-text_expect: Expected because I was paying a lot of money for a good quality product/service, and I have had no problems since, in fact I feel more in control when driving now and that is reassuring.

con2-text_expect: Unexpected because I spent nearly double on this camera than my last one and it is hardly an improvement. The quality of the camera is bad and the entire experience setting it all up was tough.

con1-product: Family vacation to a resort in the Bahamas
con1-text_emo1: This was our first family vacation that we took since our youngest son was born, and prior to his birth, we were used to vacationing quite a bit, if not to expensive places, at least on a frequent basis. So, needless to say, my husband and I really needed this vacation.  We found a resort that cost a bit more but that offered childcare onsite that was reputable, so it was a no brainer.  My family and I got to explore the historical and artistic parts of the culture and commune with nature, and it was wonderful to see one of my favorite places in the whole world through the eyes of my young children.
con1-text_emo2: Grateful, joyful, calm, serene, and at peace because I got away from the demands of work and full-time motherhood, and got some assistance with childcare.
con1-text_importance: Yes because I really needed to get away, having three children and working full-time is stressful and relentless.
con1-text_goalsCon: Yes because I felt safe and secure leaving my children in the daycare/kids club, I got a chance to romance with my husband, and it was fun going on adventures with my entire family.
con1-text_pleasant: Yes because we were catered to in almost every way, everyone was in a good mood, lots to do or not do.
con1-text_expect: Yes, it was better than expected because my children were really entertained in the kids club and were in a good mood for most of the vacation.
con2-text_emo1: It does not have as much room as my previous model, and the freezer is small.  There are shelving height limitations that make it hard to store a lot of food.

con2-text_pleasant: No because it is worse than my previous refrigerator and it was still really pricey.
con2-text_expect: Unexpected because I did not realize the shelf height was so low and that it was not deep enough to store and easily find food.

con1-text_emo1: I really like iced drinks, both soft drinks such as juice, iced tea and so on as well as iced alcoholic drinks. Where I was living had a very small freezer so there wasn’t much room for ice trays. I researched the options and purchased an ice maker. I was delighted because it could make the equivalent of two trays of ice in less than 20 minutes. For the 4 months it worked, it was was great and I was very happy. Unfortunately it quit working and further research showed this happened to a lot of other purchasers. The warranty was for only 3 months with no chance of return and I could not find any information on how to repair it. I was very disappointed as it was relatively expensive. I tried repairing it myself but was unable to determine what caused it to stop working. I was very frustrated at a product that I liked had broken after so short a time.
con1-text_emo2: I was joyful because I like ice so much, even when it is very cold out and it was so quick to mark. I was frustrated and disappointed when it stopped working as I had saved up for the ic mur and could not afford to replace it, especially as I didn’t want to buy the same type, which I found under many brand names. The other options, which seemed to have a much longer life, were 3-4 times as expensive.
con1-text_importance: Yes, because I like to drink cold drinks, whether it’s water, iced tea or cocktails.
con1-text_goalsCon: Yes, because while it worked it performed very well. Then no because it quit working after only a few months.
con1-text_pleasant: Yes, because it was so fast and I didn’t need to give up space in my freezer for ice trays.
con1-text_expect: As expected because it works so quickly. Then unexpected because I expect appliances to last for many years and this one only lasted four months.
con2-text_emo1: I had a smaller and less expensive iPad that was a few year old and wants to replace it with a full sized one. I no longer had a laptop and used the iPad instead so a bigger screen to function more as a computer wa important to me. I went to the Apple Store, looked over the high end Pro models and purchased one with the most memory as I expected to keep it for several years. It’s now been more than 4 years and I’m typing this on that Sam iPad. It wa a very good choice as far as storage spac, functionality and screen quality go and it works for everything from reading news to reading books to watching movies.
con2-text_emo2: The size of the screen is bigger than most laptops and the resolution and clarity make watching movies and playing games a delight.
con2-text_importance: Yes because I switched over to reading only ebooks years ago as I don’t have space for print books where I live. I also enjoy being able to take many books with me wherever I go.
con2-text_goalsCon: Yes because the screen clarity, range of colors and resolution is so much better than I expected, far better than the laptop it replaced.
con2-text_pleasant: Yes, because it operates quickly, I do not encounter any of the system problems I had with a Windows-based PC and it is easy to use.
con2-text_expect: Expected because I have had other Apple iPhones and iPads and all have worked quite well. This one was even better than expected because of its large screen, large storage capacity and great resolution.

con1-text_emo1: When I started using the laptop and doing all the things I normally did on my old laptop - browse the internet, play some video games, chat with friends on Discord, and so forth. It all felt so much nicer on this new machine compared to my previous laptop purchased in 2015. The screen was higher quality, the trackpad was better, the increased performance allowed it to run more smoothly, and the battery life was much longer. Everything made me feel like I had made the right choice in buying this product.
con1-text_emo2: I felt like I had made the right choice when I bought this laptop. I was hesitant to buy a new one, due to the cost, and literally waited until my old one was unsafe to use to purchase this new laptop. I was just happy this new machine could do everything I wanted to do so effortlessly.
con1-text_importance: Yes because my laptop is crucial to almost everything I do, from socializing to web browsing to working. If I am not using my phone then I am using my laptop, so it is important to me that this device work as well as possible.
con1-text_goalsCon: Yes because it more than met my expectations for how I wanted this machine to run and operate normally.
con1-text_pleasant: Yes because it effortlessly handled all the usual tasks I carry out on a laptop.
con1-text_expect: Expected because I had read plenty of reviews and was decently familiar with the experience that I would be getting from this computer.
con2-text_emo1: I was disappointed in the quality of this monitor. I bought it for the gaming PC I built, after looking thru many online reviews touting this monitor's quality and value. The monitor itself worked fine at first but within a few months it developed a few dead pixels, which are especially distracting. This issue only got worse as more dead pixels developed on the monitor. What made this worse was the fact that the warranty didn't cover dead pixels either, so I was stuck with this expensive, flawed monitor.
con2-text_emo2: I felt disappointed because it wasn't an unsubstantial amount of money I spent on this monitor and I had hoped it would last several years without issue.
con2-text_importance: Yes because I needed it to use the gaming PC I built, otherwise the PC would be fairly useless.
con2-text_goalsCon: No because I wanted a monitor that would last me for years and this monitor only lasted a few months before developing an issue.
con2-text_pleasant: No because it was impossible to ignore the dead pixels while using the monitor, such that it pissed me off every time I saw them on the screen.
con2-text_expect: Unexpected because all the reviews I read online were positive and no one seemed to have experienced a failure like this as soon as I did.

con1-text_expect: Unexpected, because I expected the rates being demanded to equate with a commensurate level of experience and ability. Although I admit the matter is not fully resolved so I suppose there is still some hope things will turn out better than I currently expect.

con1-text_emo1: I am not coping well with the fact that age is starting to take a toll on my looks, especially facial wrinkles and loss of volume.  The NIRA Home use laser is a small, approved device to help rebuild some of the collagen under the skin that depletes with age.  I was so excited to receive a discount code of 50% off right after Thanksgiving and ordered the device.  I had to wait 2 months for the product to be shipped.  I felt that for what it cost, the wait to receive it was overly long.  I was very disappointed with the delay feeling the manufacturer should have predicted the large numbers of orders due to the time of year and wonderful discount they were offering.  I was on the verge of cancelling the order when I finally received a message that it would ship to me within 7 days.  When I finally got the unit, I was greatly surprised at how simple it really was to use, and how the pain/discomfort I was expecting using it did not happen.
con1-text_emo2: Like most people today, I have gotten use to very quick service and fast shipping (usually a day or two).  I started to have doubts about the legitimacy of the company itself, and was reading online about many other purchasers who were feeling the same way.  There were also many reports of people who stated the product was too powerful and painful when used around the eyes, which was where I was intending to use it.  So I was pleasantly surprised when there was no pain at all, only a slight warming sensation.
con1-text_importance: Yes because overall I don't feel my age, I usually feel about 15-20 years younger both mentally and in other physical attributes (I am petite in stature and slightly underweight).  So it is very important to me to try to look my best, especially in my face which, of course, everyone sees all the time.  I want to continue to have my 'exterior' reflect how I feel on my 'interior' if that makes sense.
con1-text_goalsCon: Yes because while most women will visit a plastic surgeon or cosmetic dermatologist to have very similar procedures done professionally, the cost of those treatments/procedures is extremely high (in the thousands of dollars) and is something that has to be done often (every 6 to 12 months).  There is also some 'down time' where they have to take a couple days off work for the skin to heal.  Also, if the professional makes a mistake, the damage can be unrepairable.  So lots of risk.  This device was a lower level laser, so much safer to use, the trade off being it might take a couple extra weeks to achieve the same result.  But less risk and less cost overall.
con1-text_pleasant: Yes because it is very simple to use, absolutely no discomfort/pain, much less time involved (5 to 10 minutes, once or twice a day) versus having to make office appointments which can take several hours each time.
con1-text_expect: Unexpected because while the product is designed specifically for the eye areas, several other users recommended it for the lines around the lips due to smoking.  I have been a smoker for over 30 years and have deep lines in that area.  I did try the product there and am pleasantly surprised that it has made a great improvement in filling in/removing those wrinkles.
con2-text_emo1: I suffer from scoliosis (curvature of the spine) and the pain can be very bad.  A chiropractor recommended using a vibrating unit a few times a week to keep muscles in my spinal area exercised and loose.  I purchased a highly rated machine, used it for a couple weeks, and now do not experience the back pain I had for years, especially first thing in the mornings.
con2-text_emo2: It is very similar to having a massage at a spa, so very relaxing and pleasant.
con2-text_importance: Yes because body pains can put you in a negative mood, and that is reflected in how to deal with/treat others, how well you perform your job, etc.
con2-text_goalsCon: Yes because it does relieve my pain, has paid for itself 20 times over versus office visits saving me lots of time and money.
con2-text_pleasant: Yes it is a pleasant experience when using it.  Like a massage, a rather strange tingling feeling until you get used to it.  I look forward to using it.
con2-text_expect: Expected because I trust my chiropractor to advise me what to do and not do, I trust his judgment.

con1-text_emo1: I bought the dress using the first disposable income I'd ever had in my adult life. I bought it from a store I'd never been able to shop at before, after having lost some weight (Free People). The cut of the dress was inspired, with a slight empire waist and an elaborated threaded design along the breast of the top. It was impossible for me to ignore the quality of the fabric itself, being far and above anything else I owned. The color matched my eyes, and it had both a casual air about it and this flattering classy element, that I just hadn't experienced before. I could just as easily wear it to the beach as to a fancy brunch or a night out. The combination of all those things made me feel prideful as soon as I carried it out the store and for months after purchasing.
con1-text_emo2: I knew that not only had I worked hard at my job to save and earn enough to finally spend some money on my clothes outside of some fast fashion outlet but also that I had lost a significant amount of weight prior to purchasing, so it was like I was crowning this personal achievement in a private moment. Wearing it out, I'd be the only person aware of this association but I imagine in hindsight that probably lent itself to how well I wore it. I was immensely proud of that dress.
con1-text_importance: Yes because it had been so rare for me to feel sexy and unencumbered when looking for clothes, for both financial and weight-related reasons. I'm someone who has long had an appreciation for fashion and has only had the ability to indulge that impulse for the last few years. So, it felt novel and exciting to be able to participate in something that others tend to take for granted.
con1-text_goalsCon: Neutral because my tastes have changed a little since then so there's a chance I wouldn't have purchased the same dress if asked to do so now. I wasn't sure what I wanted, only that I wanted to spend some dough and feel fancy. Nowadays, I might be more particular.
con1-text_pleasant: Yes because of how beautiful it made me feel, how exciting it felt to have earned this private sense of accomplishment, and also the texture of the fabric and the cut of the dress made it a joy to wander around in. Very flowy.
con1-text_expect: Expected because I expect a dress that costs more than $200 to be of above-average quality, to last an for years, and to be more timeless than trendy (if possible).
con2-product: the Willis Tower (formerly Sears Tower) observation deck
con2-text_emo1: I think this purchase was plagued by unmet expectations. I'd heard a lot about the observation deck at Willis Tower and, being a new resident to Chicago at the time, it seemed like a fun excursion for the family. It was completely disappointing. Boring, crowded... the best part of the entire experience was the elevator ride to the top. Literally. The elevator ride. It was so crowded by the time my family and I were able to nab a spot on the "deck" overhang, we had less than 3 minutes before the eager faces of the lines of other families were already shuffling us off. A quick snapshot and it was over. $60 a head for 2 minutes, a photograph, and, "Oh, wow, yeah, that's high up in the air." Disappointing is the word, definitely.
con2-text_emo2: When doing tourist-y things you expect to deal with other tourists but the reward was so small, the energy and price so high, it was an incredibly irritating, annoying experience. I was disappointed because I thought I was paying for some guaranteed, bucketlist-crossing, shared fun. It wasn't like that at all. It was standing on tiptoes to try and peek over other peoples' heads at a skyline and then having a minute at the skyline and not even really having the time or space to appreciate said skyline... and also, everyone smells. Like, way too crowded. It sucked.
con2-text_importance: Yes because it was shared family time. My family always kinda struggles to have a good time on vacation, either due to cost or mutual, inevitable frustration. I wanted to contribute to a good time and instead I ended up wasting 3 hours and almost $400 waiting in line not really talking to one another. I wanted it to be a happy memory and it's not like it was the worst experience I've ever had but instead it was like another snapshot of mild embarrassment and moderate disappointment in a family photo album full of bummers.
con2-text_goalsCon: No because it was/is absolutely a tourist trap. Like, a real tourist trap. Something you could easily skip. I'd rather ride the elevator up and down all those floors for a half hour than hang around trying to get a good view on the observation deck. Boring as hell.
con2-text_pleasant: No because it failed to meet any expectations of entertainment, bonding, or awe. It failed to meet its own advertised hype.
con2-text_expect: Unexpected because I assumed that with the ticket price and what I'd heard about it via word of mouth that we'd actually have had some time to hang out on the overhang and take in the world-famous view. The most space we had from the large, waiting crowd was about 3-4 feet as we took our 2-3 minutes of overhang time. Otherwise we were in close proximity to others, with human bodies completely drowning out the potential view.

I decided that I wouldn't disclose the price because he would try to refuse it and have me return it if he knew how much I paid, but I felt it was a great deal as it was wireless and rechargeable, with a single charge lasting 8-10 hours, plus it came with 3 different clip types. One for facial hair, one for body hair, and the last for his head. I got home and gave it to him and he was so excited. He opened it up and read the instructions for charging and other important information. He placed it on the charger and set the timer on his phone for the length of time it needed to charge. When the timer went off we removed it from the charger and got set up for me to cut his hair. I started to shave his head and didn't make it half way even before it was completely dead. We plugged it back in only in a different outlet and double checked the charging times. Again we wait for the timer and try to finish shaving his head to again have it die before finishing. con1-text_emo1: I have mixed emotions about buying and wearing my expensive suit. On one hand, I felt a sense of joy and pride when I first saw myself in the mirror. The suit fit me like a glove, and the fabric felt luxurious against my skin. I felt like a million bucks and was excited to show off my new look to everyone I knew. con1-product: I went to Hawaii on vacation last summer.
con1-text_emo1: I had a wonderful time in Hawaii because of the beautiful beaches, forests, and volcanoes. The people there were really friendly and made me feel welcome. I loved trying out new things like surfing and snorkeling, and the food was delicious. The best part was being able to relax and enjoy the peaceful atmosphere. Overall, my trip to Hawaii brought me a lot of joy
con1-text_emo2: I felt happy on the trip to Hawaii for a few reasons. The beautiful beaches, forests, and volcanoes made me amazed and appreciative. The people there were really nice and made me feel welcome, which made me feel good. I had fun doing exciting things like surfing and snorkeling. The food was really tasty and different from what I usually have. Lastly, just relaxing and enjoying the peaceful surroundings in Hawaii made me feel really happy.
con1-text_importance: Yes, because the trip to Hawaii was important to me it provided a much-needed break and allowed me to escape from my daily routine and responsibilities. It gave me a chance to relax, rejuvenate, and recharge. Exploring the natural beauty of Hawaii and engaging in exciting activities provided a sense of adventure and new experiences. It was an opportunity to create lasting memories and connect with the local culture and traditions. The trip allowed me to step out of my comfort zone, try new things, and broaden my horizons. Overall, it was a valuable and memorable experience that enriched my life.
con1-text_goalsCon:
Yes, because the trip to Hawaii was consistent with what I wanted.

The trip aligned with my desires and expectations because I was seeking a destination with beautiful natural landscapes, and Hawaii delivered just that. The stunning beaches, lush forests, and volcanic formations exceeded my expectations and fulfilled my desire for picturesque scenery. I also wanted a mix of relaxation and adventure, and Hawaii provided the perfect balance. I had the opportunity to unwind on the beaches, indulge in spa treatments, and enjoy peaceful moments, while also engaging in thrilling activities like surfing, snorkeling, and exploring the outdoors. The vibrant local culture and cuisine were additional elements I sought, and I was able to immerse myself in Hawaiian traditions, try delicious food, and interact with friendly locals. Overall, the trip to Hawaii met my expectations and offered everything I had hoped for.
con1-text_pleasant:
Yes, because it was a pleasant experience when I was on the trip.

It was a pleasant experience because the natural beauty of Hawaii was captivating and brought me joy. The stunning beaches, lush forests, and volcanic landscapes created a picturesque setting that was truly enjoyable. The friendly and welcoming nature of the local people added to the pleasantness of the trip. Their warmth and hospitality made me feel comfortable and happy during my stay. Engaging in exciting activities like surfing and snorkeling was thrilling and brought a sense of adventure. Exploring the vibrant local culture, trying delicious Hawaiian cuisine, and taking in the relaxed and peaceful atmosphere further contributed to the overall pleasantness of the trip.
con1-text_expect:
During the trip, some things turned out just like I expected, while others caught me off guard.

The natural beauty of Hawaii, like the amazing beaches and lush forests, was exactly what I had imagined. I had seen all those stunning pictures online, so I knew it was going to be beautiful, and it totally lived up to the hype.

The locals being friendly was also as I expected. People had told me about the Aloha spirit and how welcoming Hawaiians are, so I wasn't surprised when I met so many friendly and nice folks.

But there were a few unexpected things too. The sheer magnitude of the natural beauty was mind-blowing. No picture or video could capture the real beauty of those landscapes. Being there in person was a whole new level of awe.

And let's talk about the food! I had heard the food in Hawaii was good, but man, it blew me away. The flavors and combinations were so unique and delicious. Trying dishes like poke bowls and shave ice was a tasty surprise.

All in all, the trip had its expected moments and some pleasant surprises, making it even more memorable.
con2-text_emo1: My experience at that expensive restaurant was quite disappointing. While the initial impression was positive, the overall service quickly became lackluster and inattentive. It took a long time to place our order, and when the food finally arrived, it was lukewarm and underwhelming. The flavors lacked depth, the presentation was average, and the portion sizes were surprisingly small. Considering the high prices, I expected a more memorable culinary experience. Unfortunately, the restaurant fell short of my expectations and I left feeling unsatisfied both in terms of taste and value. If you're looking for an exceptional dining experience, I would recommend exploring other options that offer better quality and value for your money.
con2-text_emo2:
I felt disappointed for several reasons. Firstly, the service was not up to par. Despite the initial friendly greeting, the staff seemed disinterested and inattentive throughout the evening. Slow response times and a lack of attentiveness made the dining experience less enjoyable.

Secondly, the food itself did not meet my expectations. Given the reputation and prices of the restaurant, I anticipated a higher level of culinary excellence. However, the flavors were lacking in depth and the presentation was underwhelming. It felt like the dishes lacked creativity and the quality fell short of what I had hoped for.

Furthermore, the portion sizes were surprisingly small. Considering the prices charged at this expensive restaurant, I expected more generous portions. Leaving the restaurant feeling hungry and unsatisfied added to my disappointment.

Lastly, the overall value for money was lacking. The high prices on the menu did not align with the quality of the food and dining experience. I felt like I was paying a premium simply for the restaurant's reputation, rather than receiving a truly exceptional and memorable dining experience.

In summary, the combination of subpar service, underwhelming food, small portions, and the feeling of not getting good value for the price led to my disappointment with the restaurant.

con1-text_emo1:
I rented a cabin just recently, about two weeks ago actually. When I arrived with my S.O. it wasn't exactly as pictured on their website. The scenic view of the lake was exactly like the pictures. However, the cabin we were staying at looked about 10-20 years older than the pictures. The basketball hoop in the driveway was rusted and decayed, and the forest scenery behind the cabin had a bunch of old trucks, and boats just rotting away in the background. There was also an old condemned house just below our cabin and another condemned house further out behind our cabin. 

It was disturbing like some "Cabin in the Woods/Hills have eyes" shit. We also couldn't park our car in the garage. The garage door was locked from the inside, and there were black garbage bags over the windows, which made it seem even creepier. The cabin inside looked like someone's grandmother's house. So overall, it was pretty disappointing.
con1-text_emo2: The product/service was not what I paid for, therefore I felt disappointed with what I received.
con1-text_importance: Yes, it was supposed to be an important experience, because, it was our 10th anniversary.
con1-text_goalsCon: No, because the product/service was not as described and or pictured at the time of purchase.
con1-text_pleasant: Neutral, It wasn't a BAD experience, however, it wasn't GOOD either. The cabin I rented was not as described on the website, which was a letdown. We were supposed to also have our own private dock. Which we did not have. So it definitely killed our mood when we got there. But we ended up making the best of it and having fun anyway.
con1-text_expect: Unexpected because the outdoor scenery around the cabin wasn't as described. We didn't have our own dock which was stated, and the state of the property was in a bit of decay. So a lot of it was unexpected.

con1-text_emo1: I had never installed my own computer components before and had always just bought pre-made computers. This time I bought the computer parts separately and went through the trial of taking out my old parts and installing the new ones. Although there was great difficulty in the installation process for a few reasons I was ultimately successful. My computer had underwent a massive upgrade and I proved to myself that I was capable of this undertaking which is why I felt a measure of pride every time I booted up that computer from then onward.
con1-text_emo2: I had proven myself capable of computer repair, maintenance and upkeep, and had overcome my own inexperience and several other technical errors during the installation process.
con1-text_importance: Yes because my computer is my main source of entertainment, socialization, and the place I get my work done. My computer can't work without its inner workings and at the time it was in dire need of an upgrade. The parts themselves were the physical embodiment of that upgrade and my ability to keep using my computer in all the ways that I want to so they had a good degree of importance.
con1-text_goalsCon: No because while the end result I wanted ultimately ended up being achieved the installation process proved far harder than I thought it would be due to defects with the parts I had ordered. It took me hours to realize it was the parts causing the computer issues rather than my lack of ability which made for a miserable experience. Once the parts were replaced I was able to install them with little issue which is what I wanted form the start.
con1-text_pleasant: I lean towards yes that it was a pleasant experience as the parts lasted for years compared to the day or two of trouble I had with their installation. The non-defective parts worked perfectly and kept my computer top of the line for a few years longer.
con1-text_expect: Unexpected due to the difficulty of installation because I did not know the first batch of parts I had bought were defective. This made it so they wouldn't work while installed correctly. However once it was discovered that this was the error things became much easier as I had them replaced and the situation played out like I had wanted all along with the parts being relatively easy to install and their everyday use being everything I wanted and expected.
con2-text_emo1:
The VR headset I purchased was sort of the opposite of my previous experience in that it was very easy to use and setup but it didn't really match my expectation and there were unexpected difficulties that made me not want to use it. The key emotion I felt was disappointment and that was mainly due to the fact that I had no idea just how badly and how quickly VR gaming would make me feel motion sick.

The first game that I played that allowed the player to move freely messed me up so badly that I was only able to play for a few minutes before having to take the headset off and lie down for a few HOURS. I forced myself to try a few times more but it just felt like I couldn't get used to it and ended up having to medicate with myself with dramamine just to be able to play the game for extended periods. I really liked the idea of VR games but I just wasn't and am still not willing to take medication just to be able to play video games without intense sickness.
con2-text_emo2: The device made me sick to use. While motion sickness was the main concern I also found that the screens within the headset sort of hurt my eyes due to their low quality and gave eyestrain pretty quickly. It was supremely disappointing that a device meant for fun had so many different ways to make me sick and miserable.
con2-text_importance: Yes because it was a rather expensive purchase and this was when VR was getting really popular and all my friends were getting into it. They too reported some difficulties in adjustment but they all got over it in a day or two while I seemingly was never able to. I forced myself to play through mounting sickness just to get some enjoyment from the device and to play some games with them.
con2-text_goalsCon: No because the device made me sick to use it and I was never able to get over it. I was expecting some degree of difficulty in adjusting at first but I absolutely wasn't expecting to still be floored with intense motion sickness within a few minutes even after few weeks or months of use.
con2-text_pleasant: No because of the aforementioned sickness. The games I bought for the device were fun to play but I could not derive enjoyment of them for any real length of time due to the nausea, headaches, and eyestrain that playing them brought me.
con2-text_expect: Unexpected because I was not able to overcome the sickness associated with using VR for the first time. As I mentioned already I fully expected some minor difficulties adjusting, but I wasn't expecting such intense sickness or being unable to overcome it even after repeated exposure. The product itself was consistent and within expectation but the user experience just absolutely wasn't.
